{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3195, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3195", "issue_numbers": [3193], "base_commit": "fe7565f18906a21004abe91bff0e2c8a9cdc0aa7", "patch": "diff --git a/cx_Freeze/freezer.py b/cx_Freeze/freezer.py\nindex 560c5321b..3de0233f6 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/freezer.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/freezer.py\n@@ -274,6 +274,8 @@ def _copy_file(\n     def _copy_package_data(self, module: Module, target_dir: Path) -> None:\n         \"\"\"Copy any non-Python files to the target directory.\"\"\"\n         ignore_patterns = [\n+            \"*.c\",\n+            \"*.cpp\",\n             \"*.pxd\",\n             \"*.py\",\n             \"*.pyc\",\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/test_freezer.py b/tests/test_freezer.py\nindex 14a9bf092..e488dedfd 100644\n--- a/tests/test_freezer.py\n+++ b/tests/test_freezer.py\n@@ -369,6 +369,8 @@ def test_freezer_copy_package_data(tmp_package) -> None:\n     result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\"Hello from cx_Freeze\")\n \n     ignore_patterns = [\n+        \"*.c\",\n+        \"*.cpp\",\n         \"*.pxd\",\n         \"*.py\",\n         # \"*.pyc\", # this pattern is not copied by _copy_package_data itself.\n", "problem_statement": "Excluding files\nHello! Thanks for this great tool!\n\nHow can I exclude files matching a pattern before building the macOS app bundle?\nAlternatively, is there a way to run a custom script between `build_exe` and `bdist_mac`, like it done for `bdist_appimage` with `skip_build` parameter?\n\nI am compiling my `.py` files with Cython and want to distribute only the `.so` files. However, `build_exe` is currently including both `.cpp` and `.so` files, whereas I only need the `.so` files.\n", "hints_text": "cx_Freeze 8.4.1+ does not copy Cython files (PR #3084). I can expand the list to include .c and .cpp. I'll evaluate that and should do a PR this weekend.\n\nI recommend the use of the latest version 8.5.0.\n\nFor a local solution, I believe you could run a script after bdist_mac and delete the files within the structure. The files are located in folders under Contents/MacOS/lib.\n\nYes, cx_Freeze does not copy the source Cython files, but it copies the intermediate .cpp files generated by cythonize. While I can manually remove them from Contents/MacOS/lib, I cannot do the same for AppImage or MSI builds.\n\nIt would be great to add a parameter like \"scan-packages\" to limit scanning to specific packages and only add their dependencies to the lib directory.\nFor appimage and msi you can use build_exe, exclude the files, then bdist_appimage --skip-build.\nThe same for msi.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "cx_Freeze 8.4.1+ does not copy Cython files (PR #3084). I can expand the list to include .c and .cpp. I'll evaluate that and should do a PR this weekend.\n\nI recommend the use of the latest version 8.5.0.\n\nFor a local solution, I believe you could run a script after bdist_mac and delete the files within the structure. The files are located in folders under Contents/MacOS/lib.\n\nYes, cx_Freeze does not copy the source Cython files, but it copies the intermediate .cpp files generated by cythonize. While I can manually remove them from Contents/MacOS/lib, I cannot do the same for AppImage or MSI builds.\n\nIt would be great to add a parameter like \"scan-packages\" to limit scanning to specific packages and only add their dependencies to the lib directory.\nFor appimage and msi you can use build_exe, exclude the files, then bdist_appimage --skip-build.\nThe same for msi.\nBut, before you create a script, test the new PR 3195\nYou can test the PR with:\n`pip install git+https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze.git@refs/pull/3195/head`\nor\n`pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.0.PR.*\"`\nUsing uv:\n`uv pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.0.PR.*\" --index-strategy unsafe-best-match`\n\nIt works properly. Thank you!\n[Release 8.5.1](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/releases/tag/8.5.1) is out!\n[Documentation](https://cx-freeze.readthedocs.io)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/60170aab81409896ef96b92b7f7e414add07a54c", "https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/97fb8bd603a82a2c4d7a636cc367dff35c428454"], "created_at": "2025-12-05T17:41:05Z"}
{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3235, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3235", "issue_numbers": [3233], "base_commit": "0971e3fd656ab60fd92dbcf93f0a0ae694302167", "patch": "diff --git a/cx_Freeze/command/bdist_msi.py b/cx_Freeze/command/bdist_msi.py\nindex 637a7627b..078a85215 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/command/bdist_msi.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/command/bdist_msi.py\n@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@\n import os\n import re\n import shutil\n+from contextlib import suppress\n from typing import ClassVar\n \n from packaging.version import Version\n@@ -100,39 +101,90 @@ class bdist_msi(Command):\n             \"skip rebuilding everything (for testing/debugging)\",\n         ),\n         # cx_Freeze specific\n-        (\"add-to-path=\", None, \"add target dir to PATH environment variable\"),\n-        (\"all-users=\", None, \"installation for all users (or just me)\"),\n+        (\n+            \"add-to-path=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"add target directory to the PATH environment variable \"\n+            \"[default: False]\",\n+        ),\n+        (\n+            \"all-users=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"install for all users or just for the installing user \"\n+            \"[default: False]\",\n+        ),\n         (\n             \"data=\",\n             None,\n             \"dictionary of data indexed by table name, and each value is a \"\n             \"tuple to include in table\",\n         ),\n-        (\"directories=\", None, \"list of 3-tuples of directories to create\"),\n-        (\"environment-variables=\", None, \"list of environment variables\"),\n+        (\n+            \"directories=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"list of 3-tuples of directories that should be created during \"\n+            \"installation\",\n+        ),\n+        (\n+            \"environment-variables=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"list of environment variables that should be added to the \"\n+            \"system during installation\",\n+        ),\n         (\"extensions=\", None, \"Extensions for which to register Verbs\"),\n         (\"initial-target-dir=\", None, \"initial target directory\"),\n-        (\"install-icon=\", None, \"icon path to add/remove programs \"),\n-        (\"product-code=\", None, \"product code to use\"),\n         (\n-            \"summary-data=\",\n+            \"install-icon=\",\n             None,\n-            \"Dictionary of data to include in msi summary data stream. \"\n-            'Allowed keys are \"author\", \"comments\", \"keywords\".',\n+            \"path of icon to use for the add/remove programs\",\n+        ),\n+        (\n+            \"launch-on-finish\",\n+            None,\n+            \"include a 'Launch on Finish' checkbox in the installer\"\n+            \"[default: False]\",\n         ),\n-        (\"target-name=\", None, \"name of the file to create\"),\n-        (\"target-version=\", None, \"version of the file to create\"),\n-        (\"upgrade-code=\", None, \"upgrade code to use\"),\n         (\n             \"license-file=\",\n             None,\n-            \"rft formatted license file to include in the installer\",\n+            \"path to a rtf formmated file to be used as the license agreement\",\n         ),\n         (\n-            \"launch-on-finish\",\n+            \"output-name=\",\n             None,\n-            \"Include a Launch on Finish checkbox in the installer.\",\n+            \"specifies the name of the file that is to be created\",\n         ),\n+        (\n+            \"product-code=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"define the product code for the package that is created\",\n+        ),\n+        (\n+            \"product-name=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"define the product name for the package that is created \"\n+            \"[default: metadata name]\",\n+        ),\n+        (\n+            \"product-version=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"define the product version for the package that is created \"\n+            \"[default: metadata version if available]\",\n+        ),\n+        (\n+            \"summary-data=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"dictionary of data to include in MSI summary data stream \"\n+            '(allowed keys are \"author\", \"comments\" and \"keywords\")',\n+        ),\n+        (\n+            \"upgrade-code=\",\n+            None,\n+            \"define the GUID of the upgrade code for the package that is \"\n+            \"created\",\n+        ),\n+        (\"target-name=\", None, \"[removed]\"),\n+        (\"target-version=\", None, \"[removed]\"),\n     ]\n \n     boolean_options: ClassVar[list[str]] = [\n@@ -398,7 +450,8 @@ def add_exit_dialog(self) -> None:\n                         \"VSDCA_Launch\",\n                         226,\n                         \"TARGETDIR\",\n-                        f\"[TARGETDIR]\\\\{self.distribution.executables[0].target_name}\",\n+                        \"[TARGETDIR]\\\\\"\n+                        f\"{self.distribution.executables[0].target_name}\",\n                     )\n                 ],\n             )\n@@ -1043,23 +1096,27 @@ def initialize_options(self) -> None:\n         self.skip_build = None\n         self.install_script = None\n         self.pre_install_script = None\n+        self.fullname = None\n         # cx_Freeze specific\n-        self.upgrade_code = None\n-        self.product_code = None\n         self.add_to_path = None\n-        self.initial_target_dir = None\n-        self.target_name = None\n-        self.target_version = None\n-        self.fullname = None\n+        self.all_users = False\n+        self.data = None\n         self.directories = None\n         self.environment_variables = None\n-        self.data = None\n-        self.summary_data = None\n-        self.install_icon = None\n-        self.all_users = False\n         self.extensions = None\n-        self.license_file = None\n+        self.initial_target_dir = None\n+        self.install_icon = None\n         self.launch_on_finish = None\n+        self.license_file = None\n+        self.output_name = None\n+        self.product_code = None\n+        self.product_name = None\n+        self.product_version = None\n+        self.summary_data = None\n+        self.upgrade_code = None\n+        # removed\n+        self.target_name = None\n+        self.target_version = None\n \n         self._warnings = []\n \n@@ -1095,47 +1152,44 @@ def finalize_options(self) -> None:\n                 raise OptionError(msg)\n         self.install_script_key = None\n \n-        # default values for target_name and target_version\n-        if self.target_name is None:\n-            if self.distribution.metadata.name:\n-                self.target_name = self.distribution.metadata.name\n-            else:\n-                executables = self.distribution.executables\n-                executable = executables[0]\n-                self.warn_delayed(\n-                    \"using the first executable as target_name: \"\n-                    f\"{executable.target_name}\"\n-                )\n-                self.target_name = executable.target_name\n-        if self.target_version is None and self.distribution.metadata.version:\n-            self.target_version = self.distribution.metadata.version\n-\n-        name = self.target_name\n-        version = self.target_version\n-        name, ext = os.path.splitext(name)\n-        if ext == \".msi\":\n-            self.msi_name = self.target_name\n-            self.fullname = name\n-        elif version:\n-            self.msi_name = f\"{name}-{version}-{MSI_PLATFORM}.msi\"\n-            self.fullname = f\"{name}-{version}\"\n-        else:\n-            self.msi_name = f\"{name}-{MSI_PLATFORM}.msi\"\n-            self.fullname = name\n+        # removed\n+        if self.target_name is not None:\n+            msg = (\n+                \"target_name option was removed, use output_name\"\n+                \" (or in some cases, use project.name or product_name instead)\"\n+            )\n+            raise OptionError(msg)\n+        if self.target_version is not None:\n+            msg = (\n+                \"target_version option was removed, \"\n+                \"use project.version or product_version instead\"\n+            )\n+            raise OptionError(msg)\n \n-        # default metadata name and version if not set in setup/pyproject\n+        # name is required\n         if not self.distribution.metadata.name:\n-            self.distribution.metadata.name = name.split(\"-\")[0]\n-        if not self.distribution.metadata.version:\n-            self.distribution.metadata.version = version\n-        name = self.distribution.get_name()\n+            msg = \"name is required\"\n+            raise OptionError(msg)\n+\n+        # default values for product_name and product_version\n+        self.ensure_string(\"product_name\", self.distribution.get_name())\n+        self.ensure_string(\"product_version\", self.distribution.get_version())\n+        # ProductVersion must be strictly numeric\n+        self.product_version = Version(self.product_version).base_version\n+        self.fullname = f\"{self.product_name}-{self.product_version}\"\n+        self.ensure_string(\n+            \"output_name\", f\"{self.fullname}-{MSI_PLATFORM}.msi\"\n+        )\n \n         if self.initial_target_dir is None:\n             if IS_ARM_64 or IS_X86_64:\n                 program_files_folder = \"ProgramFiles64Folder\"\n             else:\n                 program_files_folder = \"ProgramFilesFolder\"\n-            self.initial_target_dir = rf\"[{program_files_folder}]\\{name}\"\n+            self.initial_target_dir = (\n+                rf\"[{program_files_folder}]\\{self.product_name}\"\n+            )\n+        self.ensure_filename(\"install_icon\")\n         if self.add_to_path is None:\n             self.add_to_path = False\n         if self.directories is None:\n@@ -1144,6 +1198,7 @@ def finalize_options(self) -> None:\n             self.environment_variables = []\n         if self.license_file is not None:\n             self.license_file = os.path.abspath(self.license_file)\n+        self.ensure_filename(\"license_file\")\n         if self.data is None:\n             self.data = {}\n         if not isinstance(self.summary_data, dict):\n@@ -1179,7 +1234,9 @@ def finalize_options(self) -> None:\n                 )\n                 raise ValueError(msg) from None\n             stem = os.path.splitext(executable)[0]\n-            progid = make_id(f\"{name}.{stem}.{version}\")\n+            progid = make_id(\n+                f\"{self.product_name}.{stem}.{self.product_version}\"\n+            )\n             mime = extension.get(\"mime\", None)\n             # \"%1\" a better default for argument?\n             argument = extension.get(\"argument\", None)\n@@ -1207,7 +1264,7 @@ def finalize_options(self) -> None:\n                 -1,\n                 rf\"Software\\Classes\\{progid}\",\n                 \"FriendlyAppName\",\n-                name,\n+                self.product_name,\n                 component,\n             )\n             self._append_to_data(\n@@ -1216,7 +1273,7 @@ def finalize_options(self) -> None:\n                 -1,\n                 rf\"Software\\Classes\\{progid}\\shell\\{verb}\",\n                 \"FriendlyAppName\",\n-                name,\n+                self.product_name,\n                 component,\n             )\n             self._append_to_data(\n@@ -1246,17 +1303,12 @@ def run(self) -> None:\n         # make msi (by default in dist directory)\n         self.mkpath(self.dist_dir)\n         installer_name = os.path.abspath(\n-            os.path.join(self.dist_dir, self.msi_name)\n+            os.path.join(self.dist_dir, self.output_name)\n         )\n-        if os.path.exists(installer_name):\n+        with suppress(FileNotFoundError):\n             os.unlink(installer_name)\n \n         author = self.distribution.metadata.get_contact() or \"UNKNOWN\"\n-        distribution_name = self.distribution.get_name()\n-        # ProductVersion must be strictly numeric\n-        distribution_version = Version(\n-            self.target_version or self.distribution.get_version()\n-        ).base_version\n \n         # msilib is reloaded in order to reset the \"_directories\" global member\n         # in that module.  That member is used by msilib to prevent any two\n@@ -1272,20 +1324,20 @@ def run(self) -> None:\n         self.db = init_database(\n             installer_name,\n             schema,\n-            distribution_name,\n+            self.product_name,\n             self.product_code,\n-            distribution_version,\n+            self.product_version,\n             author,\n         )\n         add_tables(self.db, sequence)\n         self.add_properties()\n         self.add_config()\n-        self.add_upgrade_config(distribution_version)\n+        self.add_upgrade_config(self.product_version)\n         self.add_ui()\n         self.add_files()\n         self.db.Commit()\n         self.distribution.dist_files.append(\n-            (\"bdist_msi\", distribution_version or \"any\", distribution_name)\n+            (\"bdist_msi\", self.product_version or \"any\", self.product_name)\n         )\n \n         if not self.keep_temp:\ndiff --git a/doc/src/bdist_msi.rst b/doc/src/bdist_msi.rst\nindex fc9e41d7e..07b4404e5 100644\n--- a/doc/src/bdist_msi.rst\n+++ b/doc/src/bdist_msi.rst\n@@ -32,12 +32,10 @@ command:\n    * - option name\n      - description\n    * - .. option:: add_to_path\n-     - add the target directory to the PATH environment variable; the default\n-       value is True if there are any console-based executables and False\n-       otherwise.\n+     - add the target directory to the PATH environment variable\n+       [default: False]\n    * - .. option:: all_users\n-     - install for all users; the default value is False and results in an\n-       installation for just the installing user.\n+     - install for all users or just for the installing user [default: False]\n    * - .. option:: data\n      - dictionary of arbitrary MSI data indexed by table name; for each table,\n        a list of tuples should be provided, representing the rows that should\n@@ -65,21 +63,25 @@ command:\n        during installation.\n    * - .. option:: launch_on_finish\n      - boolean flag that includes a \"Launch the installed app on finish?\"\n-       checkbox to the final step of the installer. [default: False]\n+       checkbox to the final step of the installer [default: False]\n    * - .. option:: license_file\n-     - path to an rtf formmated file to be used as the license agreement.\n-       Refer to `Windows Installer Scrollable Text\n+     - path to a rtf formmated file to be used as the license agreement;\n+       refer to `Windows Installer Scrollable Text\n        <https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/msi/scrollabletext-control#control-attributes>`_.\n+   * - .. option:: output_name\n+     - specifies the name of the file that is to be created\n+       [default: metadata name-version-platform.msi]\n    * - .. option:: product_code\n-     - define the product code for the package that is created.\n+     - define the product code for the package that is created\n+   * - .. option:: product_name\n+     - define the product name for the package that is created\n+       [default: metadata name]\n+   * - .. option:: product_version\n+     - define the product version for the package that is created\n+       [default: metadata version if available]\n    * - .. option:: summary_data\n      - dictionary of data to include in MSI summary information stream\n        (allowable keys are \"author\", \"comments\", and \"keywords\").\n-   * - .. option:: target_name\n-     - specifies the name of the file that is to be created; if the name\n-       ends with \".msi\" then it is used verbatim, otherwise, information\n-       about the program version and platform will be added to the installer\n-       name.\n    * - .. option:: upgrade_code\n      - define the GUID of the upgrade code for the package that is created;\n        this is used to force the removal of any packages created with the same\n@@ -94,6 +96,11 @@ command:\n     :option:`license_file` option.\n .. versionadded:: 8.2\n     :option:`launch_on_finish` option.\n+.. versionadded:: 8.6\n+    :option:`output_name`, :option:`product_name`, and\n+    :option:`product_version` options.\n+.. versionremoved:: 8.6\n+    :option:`target_name` option.\n \n For example:\n \n@@ -125,6 +132,7 @@ For example:\n         environment_variables = [\n             [\"E_MYAPP_VAR\", \"=-*MYAPP_VAR\", \"1\", \"TARGETDIR\"]\n         ]\n+        product_name = \"Hello cx_Freeze\"\n         # use a different upgrade_code for your project\n         upgrade_code = \"{6B29FC40-CA47-1067-B31D-00DD010662DA}\"\n \n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/test_command_bdist_msi.py b/tests/test_command_bdist_msi.py\nindex 4f6c0348a..194e11e13 100644\n--- a/tests/test_command_bdist_msi.py\n+++ b/tests/test_command_bdist_msi.py\n@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@\n \n from cx_Freeze._compat import IS_ARM_64, IS_MINGW, IS_WINDOWS, IS_X86_64\n from cx_Freeze.command.bdist_msi import bdist_msi\n+from cx_Freeze.exception import OptionError\n \n DIST_ATTRS = {\n     \"name\": \"foo\",\n@@ -33,33 +34,67 @@ def test_bdist_msi_target_dir() -> None:\n     else:\n         expected = r\"[ProgramFilesFolder]\\foo\"\n     assert cmd.initial_target_dir == expected\n-    assert cmd.fullname == \"foo\"\n-    assert cmd.target_name == \"foo\"\n+    assert cmd.fullname == \"foo-0.0.0\"\n+    assert cmd.output_name == f\"foo-0.0.0-{MSI_PLATFORM}.msi\"\n \n \n @pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n def test_bdist_msi_target_name() -> None:\n-    \"\"\"Test the bdist_msi with extra target_name option.\"\"\"\n+    \"\"\"Test the bdist_msi with extra target_name [removed] option.\"\"\"\n     dist = Distribution(DIST_ATTRS)\n     cmd = bdist_msi(dist)\n     cmd.target_name = \"mytest\"\n+    msg = \"target_name option was removed, use output_name\"\n+    with pytest.raises(OptionError, match=msg):\n+        cmd.finalize_options()\n+\n+\n+@pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n+def test_bdist_msi_target_version() -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test the bdist_msi with extra target_version [removed] option.\"\"\"\n+    dist = Distribution(DIST_ATTRS)\n+    cmd = bdist_msi(dist)\n+    cmd.target_version = \"0.1\"\n+    msg = \"target_version option was removed,\"\n+    with pytest.raises(OptionError, match=msg):\n+        cmd.finalize_options()\n+\n+\n+@pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n+def test_bdist_msi_no_name() -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test the bdist_msi with no project name option.\"\"\"\n+    dist = Distribution(\n+        {\"executables\": [\"hello.py\"], \"script_name\": \"setup.py\"}\n+    )\n+    cmd = bdist_msi(dist)\n+    msg = \"name is required\"\n+    with pytest.raises(OptionError, match=msg):\n+        cmd.finalize_options()\n+\n+\n+@pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n+def test_bdist_msi_product_name() -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test the bdist_msi with extra product_name option.\"\"\"\n+    dist = Distribution(DIST_ATTRS)\n+    cmd = bdist_msi(dist)\n+    cmd.product_name = \"my test\"\n     cmd.finalize_options()\n     cmd.ensure_finalized()\n-    assert cmd.fullname == \"mytest\"\n-    assert cmd.target_name == \"mytest\"\n+    assert cmd.fullname == \"my test-0.0.0\"\n+    assert cmd.output_name == f\"my test-0.0.0-{MSI_PLATFORM}.msi\"\n \n \n @pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n-def test_bdist_msi_target_name_and_version() -> None:\n+def test_bdist_msi_product_name_and_version() -> None:\n     \"\"\"Test the bdist_msi with extra target options.\"\"\"\n     dist = Distribution(DIST_ATTRS)\n     cmd = bdist_msi(dist)\n-    cmd.target_name = \"mytest\"\n-    cmd.target_version = \"0.1\"\n+    cmd.product_name = \"mytest\"\n+    cmd.product_version = \"0.1\"\n     cmd.finalize_options()\n     cmd.ensure_finalized()\n     assert cmd.fullname == \"mytest-0.1\"\n-    assert cmd.target_name == \"mytest\"\n+    assert cmd.output_name == f\"mytest-0.1-{MSI_PLATFORM}.msi\"\n \n \n @pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n@@ -74,24 +109,13 @@ def test_bdist_msi_default(tmp_package) -> None:\n \n \n @pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n-def test_bdist_msi_target_name_with_extension(tmp_package) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"Test the msi_extensions sample, with a specified target_name that\n+def test_bdist_msi_output_name_with_extension(tmp_package) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test the msi_extensions sample, with a specified output_name that\n     includes an \".msi\" extension.\n     \"\"\"\n     msi_name = \"output.msi\"\n     tmp_package.create_from_sample(\"msi_extensions\")\n-    tmp_package.freeze(f\"python setup.py bdist_msi --target-name {msi_name}\")\n-    file_created = tmp_package.path / \"dist\" / msi_name\n-    assert file_created.is_file()\n-\n-\n-@pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n-def test_bdist_msi_target_name_with_extension_1(tmp_package) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"Test the msi_summary_data sample.\"\"\"\n-    msi_name = \"output.1.msi\"\n-\n-    tmp_package.create_from_sample(\"msi_summary_data\")\n-    tmp_package.freeze(f\"python setup.py bdist_msi --target-name {msi_name}\")\n+    tmp_package.freeze(f\"python setup.py bdist_msi --output-name {msi_name}\")\n     file_created = tmp_package.path / \"dist\" / msi_name\n     assert file_created.is_file()\n \n@@ -113,7 +137,7 @@ def test_bdist_msi_advanced(tmp_package) -> None:\n     msi_name = \"output.msi\"\n \n     tmp_package.create_from_sample(\"advanced\")\n-    tmp_package.freeze(f\"python setup.py bdist_msi --target-name {msi_name}\")\n+    tmp_package.freeze(f\"python setup.py bdist_msi --output-name {msi_name}\")\n     file_created = tmp_package.path / \"dist\" / msi_name\n     assert file_created.is_file()\n \n@@ -124,18 +148,7 @@ def test_bdist_msi_asmodule(tmp_package) -> None:\n     msi_name = \"output.msi\"\n \n     tmp_package.create_from_sample(\"asmodule\")\n-    tmp_package.freeze(f\"python setup.py bdist_msi --target-name {msi_name}\")\n-    file_created = tmp_package.path / \"dist\" / msi_name\n-    assert file_created.is_file()\n-\n-\n-@pytest.mark.skipif(not (IS_WINDOWS or IS_MINGW), reason=\"Windows test\")\n-def test_bdist_msi_sqlite(tmp_package) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"Test the sqlite sample.\"\"\"\n-    msi_name = \"output.msi\"\n-\n-    tmp_package.create_from_sample(\"sqlite\")\n-    tmp_package.freeze(f\"python setup.py bdist_msi --target-name {msi_name}\")\n+    tmp_package.freeze(f\"python setup.py bdist_msi --output-name {msi_name}\")\n     file_created = tmp_package.path / \"dist\" / msi_name\n     assert file_created.is_file()\n \n@@ -160,7 +173,9 @@ def test_bdist_msi_sqlite(tmp_package) -> None:\n     excludes = [\"tkinter\", \"unittest\"]\n \n     [tool.cxfreeze.bdist_msi]\n-    target_name = \"output.msi\"\n+    product_name = \"Hello cx_Freeze\"\n+    product_version = \"0.1.2.3\"\n+    output_name = \"output.msi\"\n \"\"\"\n \n \n", "problem_statement": "bdist_msi internal ProductName uses project.name that is more restrictive than setup name argument\nproject.name is pep508 identifier while setup() name argument is a full string\nhttps://peps.python.org/pep-0508/#names\nhttps://packaging.python.org/en/latest/guides/writing-pyproject-toml/#basic-information\n\n### Discussed in https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/discussions/3230\n\n<div type='discussions-op-text'>\n\n<sup>Originally posted by **kbengs** January  4, 2026</sup>\nwith `python setup.py bdist_msi`\n\nand  a setup.py like this:\n```\nsetup(name='PDF Arranger',\n      version='1.12.1',\n      description='PDF Arranger',\n```\nThe name in the resulting install dialog will be \"PDF Arranger\":\n<img width=\"249\" height=\"88\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3ad33812-6df8-4ab5-b4d7-531fb7e063b1\" />\n\nWhen a pyproject.toml like this is added:\n```\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=77.0.3\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"pdfarranger\"\n```\nThe name in the installer dialog is read from the \"name\" field. The resulting dialog looks like this:\n<img width=\"249\" height=\"88\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/13eea706-22dc-4563-9a63-51ca3fd1e51f\" />\n\nThe name is also used in \"Installed apps\" list in Windows. The name field in pyproject.toml does not support spaces. Is there any way we could have a pyproject.toml file and still have the \"PDF Arranger\" name?\n\n</div>\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "@kbengs You can test the PR with:\n`pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.3.3235.dev1768025418\"`\nUsing uv:\n`uv pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.3.3235.dev1768025418\" --index-strategy unsafe-best-match`\n\nThere are two new options product_name and product_version.\nUse in pyproject.toml:\n\n```toml\n[tool.cxfreeze.bdist_msi]\nproduct_name = \"PDF Arranger\"\n```\nI tested and it seems to work fine. Thanks!\n[Release 8.6.0](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/releases/tag/8.6.0) is out!\n[Documentation](https://cx-freeze.readthedocs.io)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/189c5943d835d72964658d2062f1b47f08d45923", "https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/a7d15a0e30f9648612a613dcf221faf03fd434cb", "https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/990e2c7b6da796d510596623fc29ffc2f7a2912b"], "created_at": "2026-01-10T04:20:28Z"}
{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3242, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3242", "issue_numbers": [3236], "base_commit": "058d9053eb13536cd400d4d56a713737ef37693e", "patch": "diff --git a/cx_Freeze/__init__.py b/cx_Freeze/__init__.py\nindex 430b28246..d78255b77 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/__init__.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/__init__.py\n@@ -91,9 +91,6 @@ def plugin_install(dist: setuptools.Distribution) -> None:\n \n     # Add build_exe as subcommand of setuptools build (plugin)\n     build = dist.get_command_obj(\"build\")\n-    build.user_options.insert(\n-        1,\n-        (\"build-exe=\", None, \"[REMOVED]\"),\n-    )\n-    build.sub_commands = [*build.sub_commands, (\"build_exe\", None)]\n+    build.user_options.insert(1, (\"build-exe=\", None, \"[REMOVED]\"))\n     build.build_exe = None\n+    build.sub_commands = [*build.sub_commands, (\"build_exe\", None)]\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/command/build_exe.py b/cx_Freeze/command/build_exe.py\nindex 460670fc8..b92f987a2 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/command/build_exe.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/command/build_exe.py\n@@ -294,6 +294,9 @@ def finalize_options(self) -> None:\n         self.optimize = int(self.optimize or 0)\n \n     def run(self) -> None:\n+        # Update the package metadata\n+        self.run_command(\"egg_info\")\n+\n         executables = self.distribution.executables\n         metadata = self.distribution.metadata\n         constants_module = ConstantsModule(\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/finder.py b/cx_Freeze/finder.py\nindex d599a2f5f..2fe72269a 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/finder.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/finder.py\n@@ -121,12 +121,13 @@ def _add_module(\n                 and module.name not in self.zip_exclude_packages\n             ) or module.name in self.zip_include_packages:\n                 module.in_file_system = 0\n-            module.cache_path = self.cache_path\n-            module.update_distribution()\n         if module.path is None and path is not None:\n             module.path = list(map(Path, path))\n         if module.file is None and filename is not None:\n             module.file = filename\n+        if module.cache_path is None:\n+            module.cache_path = self.cache_path\n+            module.update_distribution()\n         return module\n \n     @cached_property\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/test_command_build_exe.py b/tests/test_command_build_exe.py\nindex fe3394afc..5a2d7d205 100644\n--- a/tests/test_command_build_exe.py\n+++ b/tests/test_command_build_exe.py\n@@ -11,16 +11,6 @@\n from cx_Freeze.command.build_exe import build_exe\n from cx_Freeze.exception import SetupError\n \n-from .datatest import SUB_PACKAGE_TEST\n-\n-BUILD_EXE_CMD = (\n-    \"python setup.py build_exe\"\n-    \" --excludes=tkinter,unittest --include-msvcr --silent\"\n-)\n-\n-OUTPUT0 = \"Hello from cx_Freeze Advanced #{}\"\n-OUTPUT1 = \"Test freeze module #{}\"\n-\n DIST_ATTRS = {\n     \"name\": \"foo\",\n     \"version\": \"0.0\",\n@@ -391,26 +381,13 @@ def test_build_exe_script_args(\n         assert getattr(cmd_obj, option) == value\n \n \n-def test_build_exe_advanced(tmp_package) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"Test the advanced sample.\"\"\"\n-    tmp_package.create_from_sample(\"advanced\")\n-    tmp_package.freeze(BUILD_EXE_CMD)\n-\n-    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"advanced_1\")\n-    assert executable.is_file()\n-    result = tmp_package.run(executable, timeout=10)\n-    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines([OUTPUT0.format(1), OUTPUT1.format(1)])\n-\n-    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"advanced_2\")\n-    assert executable.is_file()\n-    result = tmp_package.run(executable, timeout=10)\n-    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines([OUTPUT0.format(2), OUTPUT1.format(2)])\n-\n-\n def test_build_exe_asmodule(tmp_package) -> None:\n     \"\"\"Test the asmodule sample.\"\"\"\n     tmp_package.create_from_sample(\"asmodule\")\n-    tmp_package.freeze(BUILD_EXE_CMD)\n+    tmp_package.freeze(\n+        \"python setup.py build_exe\"\n+        \" --excludes=tkinter,unittest --include-msvcr --silent\"\n+    )\n \n     executable = tmp_package.executable(\"asmodule\")\n     assert executable.is_file()\n@@ -418,32 +395,94 @@ def test_build_exe_asmodule(tmp_package) -> None:\n     result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\"Hello from cx_Freeze\")\n \n \n-OUTPUT_SUBPACKAGE_TEST = [\"This is p.p1\", \"This is p.q.q1\"]\n+SOURCE_ADV = \"\"\"\\\n+test1.py\n+    import importlib.metadata\n+    import foobar.baz\n \n+    print(\"version\", importlib.metadata.version(\"foobar\"))\n+test2.py\n+    __import__(\"second\")\n+pyproject.toml\n+    [project]\n+    name = \"foobar\"\n+    version = \"0.0.1\"\n+    description = \"Sample cx_Freeze script\"\n \n-def test_zip_include_packages(tmp_package) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"Test the simple sample with zip_include_packages option.\"\"\"\n-    source = SUB_PACKAGE_TEST[4]\n-    tmp_package.create(source)\n-    tmp_package.freeze(\n-        f\"{BUILD_EXE_CMD} --zip-exclude-packages=* --zip-include-packages=p\",\n+    [[tool.cxfreeze.executables]]\n+    script = \"test1.py\"\n+\n+    [[tool.cxfreeze.executables]]\n+    script = \"test2.py\"\n+\n+    [tool.cxfreeze.build_exe]\n+    excludes = [\"tkinter\", \"unittest\"]\n+    include_msvcr = true\n+    include_path = \"extra\"\n+    silent = true\n+foobar/__init__.py\n+    print(\"This is foobar\")\n+foobar/baz.py\n+    print(\"This is foobar.baz\")\n+extra/second.py\n+    print(\"This is second\")\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+\n+@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n+    \"zip_packages\",\n+    [None, False, True],\n+    ids=[\"\", \"zip_exclude_packages\", \"zip_include_packages\"],\n+)\n+def test_build_exe_advanced(tmp_package, zip_packages: bool | None) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test an advanced sample.\"\"\"\n+    tmp_package.create(SOURCE_ADV)\n+    pyproject = tmp_package.path / \"pyproject.toml\"\n+    buf = pyproject.read_bytes().decode().splitlines()\n+    if zip_packages is False:\n+        buf += ['zip_exclude_packages = \"*\"', 'zip_include_packages = \"\"']\n+        pyproject.write_bytes(\"\\n\".join(buf).encode(\"utf_8\"))\n+    elif zip_packages is True:\n+        buf += ['zip_include_packages = \"*\"', 'zip_exclude_packages = \"\"']\n+        pyproject.write_bytes(\"\\n\".join(buf).encode(\"utf_8\"))\n+    tmp_package.freeze()\n+\n+    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"test1\")\n+    assert executable.is_file()\n+    result = tmp_package.run(executable, timeout=10)\n+    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\n+        [\"This is foobar\", \"This is foobar.baz\", \"version 0.0.1\"]\n     )\n \n-    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"main\")\n+    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"test2\")\n     assert executable.is_file()\n     result = tmp_package.run(executable, timeout=10)\n-    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(OUTPUT_SUBPACKAGE_TEST)\n+    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines([\"This is second\"])\n \n \n-def test_zip_exclude_packages(tmp_package) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"Test the simple sample with zip_exclude_packages option.\"\"\"\n-    source = SUB_PACKAGE_TEST[4]\n-    tmp_package.create(source)\n-    tmp_package.freeze(\n-        f\"{BUILD_EXE_CMD} --zip-exclude-packages=p --zip-include-packages=*\",\n+def test_egg_info(tmp_package) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test version update.\"\"\"\n+    tmp_package.create(SOURCE_ADV)\n+    # update the version in the pyproject\n+    pyproject = tmp_package.path / \"pyproject.toml\"\n+    buf = pyproject.read_bytes().replace(b\"0.0.1\", b\"0.0.2\")\n+    pyproject.write_bytes(buf)\n+    tmp_package.freeze()\n+\n+    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"test1\")\n+    assert executable.is_file()\n+    result = tmp_package.run(executable, timeout=10)\n+    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\n+        [\"This is foobar\", \"This is foobar.baz\", \"version 0.0.2\"]\n     )\n \n-    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"main\")\n+    # new update\n+    pyproject.write_bytes(buf.replace(b\"0.0.2\", b\"0.0.3\"))\n+    tmp_package.freeze(\"cxfreeze build_exe\")\n+\n+    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"test1\")\n     assert executable.is_file()\n     result = tmp_package.run(executable, timeout=10)\n-    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(OUTPUT_SUBPACKAGE_TEST)\n+    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\n+        [\"This is foobar\", \"This is foobar.baz\", \"version 0.0.3\"]\n+    )\n", "problem_statement": "Include dist-info folder of project\nLet's say I have specified my project version only in the pyproject.toml file.\n\n```toml\n[project]\nname = \"my_app\"\nversion = \"1.2.3\"\n```\n\nIf I build a wheel package with e.g. [build.py](https://pypi.org/project/build/), I will have a `*.dist-info` folder within, that stores some metadata and I can pick my project version at runtime in a standard way with `importlib.metadata.version`.\n\n```python\nimportlib.metadata.version(\"my_app\")\n```\n\nWould it be possible to include the `*.dist-info` folder for my project also into the frozen package? So I can use the same mechanism to pick up my application version.\n\n", "hints_text": "You can generate a .egg-info in the current directory and cx_Freeze convert it to .dist-info in the frozen app:\n`pip install -e.`\nThe same for pip install . or pip install PACKAGE.whl\n\nAre you using include_path option? \n\n\n\nI checked it.\n\n## First attempt\n\nWhen running the build WITHOUT having the `pip install -e` ran before, I get the following result:\n\n<img width=\"981\" height=\"816\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8dbcc507-c035-452c-9270-b1f1a95ec7b8\" />\n\nThere is no *.dist-info folder for my package integrated in the library.zip.\n\n## Second attempt\n\nWhen running the build WITH having the `pip install -e` ran before, then the *.dist-info folder will be integrated as expected.\n\nBut there is another problem: Let's say, I have put my package in editable state with `pip install -e`. And then I do develop something and at the end I change the version info string in the pyproject.toml. This will of course not be reflected automatically in the *.dist-info data of the editable install, in e.g. the venv-environment site packages folder. So when running the cx_freeze build, the old version string is integrated. I explicitly have to run `pip install -e` again, before freezing my package. \n\nWould it possible to make this more robust? To have the *.dist-info folder ALWAYS integrated (doesn't matter if the package is in editable install mode or not). This would also ensure to have the meta data at newest state while freezing the program.\n\nMaybe cx_freeze can trigger creating the *.dist-info folder explicitly in the build directory, before freezing the package.\n\nAnd yes, I use `include_path` option. But how is this relevant here?\n\n> When running the build WITH having the `pip install -e` ran before, then the *.dist-info folder will be integrated as expected.\n\nThat's what I meant.\n\n> I explicitly have to run `pip install -e` again, before freezing my package.\n\nYes.\n\n> Maybe cx_freeze can trigger creating the *.dist-info folder explicitly in the build directory, before freezing the package.\n\nI hadn't thought of that possibility. I guess we get used to things. I do something similar; I have scripts that already execute the necessary commands, but it's an interesting idea.\n\n> And yes, I use include_path option. But how is this relevant here?\n\nUsing `include_path` and `pip install -e` might duplicate something; try also removing `include_path` for the local path.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "You can generate a .egg-info in the current directory and cx_Freeze convert it to .dist-info in the frozen app:\n`pip install -e.`\nThe same for pip install . or pip install PACKAGE.whl\n\nAre you using include_path option? \n\n\n\nI checked it.\n\n## First attempt\n\nWhen running the build WITHOUT having the `pip install -e` ran before, I get the following result:\n\n<img width=\"981\" height=\"816\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8dbcc507-c035-452c-9270-b1f1a95ec7b8\" />\n\nThere is no *.dist-info folder for my package integrated in the library.zip.\n\n## Second attempt\n\nWhen running the build WITH having the `pip install -e` ran before, then the *.dist-info folder will be integrated as expected.\n\nBut there is another problem: Let's say, I have put my package in editable state with `pip install -e`. And then I do develop something and at the end I change the version info string in the pyproject.toml. This will of course not be reflected automatically in the *.dist-info data of the editable install, in e.g. the venv-environment site packages folder. So when running the cx_freeze build, the old version string is integrated. I explicitly have to run `pip install -e` again, before freezing my package. \n\nWould it possible to make this more robust? To have the *.dist-info folder ALWAYS integrated (doesn't matter if the package is in editable install mode or not). This would also ensure to have the meta data at newest state while freezing the program.\n\nMaybe cx_freeze can trigger creating the *.dist-info folder explicitly in the build directory, before freezing the package.\n\nAnd yes, I use `include_path` option. But how is this relevant here?\n\n> When running the build WITH having the `pip install -e` ran before, then the *.dist-info folder will be integrated as expected.\n\nThat's what I meant.\n\n> I explicitly have to run `pip install -e` again, before freezing my package.\n\nYes.\n\n> Maybe cx_freeze can trigger creating the *.dist-info folder explicitly in the build directory, before freezing the package.\n\nI hadn't thought of that possibility. I guess we get used to things. I do something similar; I have scripts that already execute the necessary commands, but it's an interesting idea.\n\n> And yes, I use include_path option. But how is this relevant here?\n\nUsing `include_path` and `pip install -e` might duplicate something; try also removing `include_path` for the local path.\n@FreeHarry Can you test the PR?\n`pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.3.3242.dev1768690655\"`\nUsing uv:\n`uv pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.3.3242.dev1768690655\" --index-strategy unsafe-best-match`\n\nI installed the dev-version...\n\n<img width=\"557\" height=\"285\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6120ffa5-71bd-45ff-ace2-8f8ebf9fd519\" />\n\nBut it doesn't worked with it. Output on the command line is the same as before. There is no .dist-info directory in the resulting library.zip. And metadata is inaccessible from inside the frozen package with `importlib.metadata.version`.\n\n<img width=\"334\" height=\"244\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/41fb0cd5-dd2a-4bb3-afb7-0b8080a45419\" />\nI use for now [build.ProjectBuilder.meta_data](https://build.pypa.io/en/stable/api.html#build.ProjectBuilder.metadata_path) from the `build` package, to create the dist-info directory first, and add it to PYTHONPATH before running `cx_freeze` on my package. This is a workaround for me at the moment and the .dist-info directory will be in the resulting library.zip.\n\n```python\nprint(\"Ensure metadata is available for the builder...\")\nmetadata_path = Path(output_path, \"metadata\")\npbuilder = ProjectBuilder(project_path, sys.executable)\npbuilder.metadata_path(metadata_path)\n\n# We add the metadata folder to the PYTHONPATH, so the builder app can\n# correctly find it and can add what is needed for the package.\nenv = os.environ.copy()\nenv[\"PYTHONPATH\"] = str(metadata_path) + (\n    os.pathsep + env[\"PYTHONPATH\"] if \"PYTHONPATH\" in env else \"\"\n)\n\nprint(\"Run build with cx_freeze...\")\nargv = [sys.executable, setup_nt_path, \"build\"]\nproc = subprocess.run(argv, env=env)\nproc.check_returncode()\n\n# Remove the metadata path, since we just need it temporary.\nremove_path(metadata_path)\n```\nWhat is the command you are using to build? cxfreeze build (using pyproject), or python setup.py ...\n\n[Here](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/blob/main/tests/test_command_build_exe.py#L398) is the source of the test used to check that it is working.\n> What is the command you are using to build? cxfreeze build (using pyproject), or python setup.py ...\n\nThe `setup_nt_path` is a setup.py file which contains some specific pre- and post-processes that I need for my package, and also the usual stuff to run cx_freeze. See below...\n\n```python\nfrom cx_Freeze import Executable, setup\n\n# ... Some code in between here...\n\n# Build setup and run it.\n# Missing arguments are taken from 'pyproject.toml'.\nsetup_args = {\n    \"options\": {\n        \"build_exe\": {\n            \"build_exe\": BUILDDIR,\n            \"includes\": [],\n            \"excludes\": [\"tkinter\", \"numpy\", \"matplotlib\", \"PIL\"],\n            \"packages\": [],\n            \"replace_paths\": [(\"*\", \"\")],\n            \"path\": [\"src\"] + sys.path,\n            \"optimize\": 1,  # keep docstrings!\n            \"include_files\": pkginfo.find_pkg_data_files(PKG_DATA_MAP),\n            \"zip_include_packages\": [\"*\"],\n            \"zip_exclude_packages\": [],\n            \"include_msvcr\": False,\n            \"silent\": True,\n        },\n    },\n    \"executables\": [\n        Executable(\n            script=Path(SRCDIR, \"__main__.py\"),\n            init_script=\"console\",\n            base=\"console\",\n            target_name=NAME,\n            icon=None,\n        ),\n    ],\n}\nsetup(**setup_args)\n\n# ... Some post processing...\n```\n> [Here](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/blob/main/tests/test_command_build_exe.py#L398) is the source of the test used to check that it is working.\n\nYour test package is working as expected on my client.\n\nMy package is using the [src layout](https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/discussions/src-layout-vs-flat-layout/). Could it be the reason why it is not working?\n\nWhat I also saw is, I have a `*.egg-info` folder beside my sources (`./src/ncxswap.egg-info`). And it is re-created when cx_freeze is running. But it is not used as a source to create the dist-info folder during the run.\n> My package is using the [src layout](https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/discussions/src-layout-vs-flat-layout/). Could it be the reason why it is not working?\n\nFrom what I understand, yes.\nWith the information from the link you provided:\n\n> Here's a breakdown of the important behaviour differences between the src\nlayout and the flat layout:\n>\n> * The src layout requires installation of the project to be able to run its\n  code, and the flat layout does not.\n>\n>  This means that the src layout involves an additional step in the\n  development workflow of a project (typically, an\n  :doc:`editable installation <setuptools:userguide/development_mode>`\n  is used for development and a regular installation is used for testing).\n\nIn summary, you will need to have run `pip install -e.`\nAfter that, cx_Freeze will update the egg-info, which will be converted to dist-info in library.zip.\n\n@FreeHarry I studied the situation, and I believe I've found a way to adapt to the src-layout without using pip. It passed the tests.\nIn your setup file, you should remove the \"path\" option, since cx_Freeze will include the src normally.\n\nYou can test the PR with:\n`pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.3.3247.dev1769305930\"`\n\n> You can test the PR with:\n> `pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.3.3247.dev1769305930\"`\n\nTested the PR with the new version on two of my projects and it worked great so far. Thanks a lot!\n\nI did freeze it with and without the \"path\" option. And both produce exactly the same results. But of course if `cx_Freeze` will support src-layout by default, I can skip this to define this option in future.\n[Release 8.6.0](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/releases/tag/8.6.0) is out!\n[Documentation](https://cx-freeze.readthedocs.io)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/54211ba83ad16efb5ef95f2feecdb95c21c9b1bd"], "created_at": "2026-01-17T22:57:32Z"}
{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3238, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3238", "issue_numbers": [3237], "base_commit": "2e4e40dda1fcb373fedc31fb634872b3fa9b4a7c", "patch": "diff --git a/cx_Freeze/hooks/qthooks.py b/cx_Freeze/hooks/qthooks.py\nindex c10f4f418..c0f1a824a 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/hooks/qthooks.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/hooks/qthooks.py\n@@ -284,7 +284,10 @@ def qt_qtqml(self, finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n         name = _qt_implementation(module)\n         copy_qt_files(finder, name, \"PluginsPath\", \"qmllint\")  # pyqt6\n         copy_qt_files(finder, name, \"PluginsPath\", \"qmltooling\")\n-        copy_qt_files(finder, name, \"QmlImportsPath\", \"*\")\n+        try:\n+            copy_qt_files(finder, name, \"QmlImportsPath\", \"*\")\n+        except KeyError:\n+            copy_qt_files(finder, name, \"Qml2ImportsPath\", \"*\")\n         finder.include_module(f\"{name}.QtQuick\")\n \n     def qt_qtquick(self, finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "KeyError: 'QmlImportsPath' when freezing PyQt5 application\nWhen attempting to freeze a PyQt5 application using cx_Freeze 8.5.3 on Windows with Python 3.13.7, a KeyError occurs because the Qt5 library path `QmlImportsPath` cannot be found.\n\n**Temporary Workaround:**\nManually modifying line 287 in `.venv/Lib/site-packages/cx_Freeze/hooks/qthooks.py` from:\n```python\ncopy_qt_files(finder, name, \"QmlImportsPath\", \"*\")\n```\nto:\n```python\ncopy_qt_files(finder, name, \"Qml2ImportsPath\", \"*\")\n```\n\n**Analysis:**\nThe issue appears to stem from cx_Freeze using the Qt6-specific library path constant `QmlImportsPath` when working with Qt5. In Qt5.15, the correct constant is `Qml2ImportsPath` (which exists but is deprecated in Qt6).\n\n**Proposed Solution:**\nModify the `qt_qtqml` function in `qthooks.py` to handle the KeyError exception gracefully. When `QmlImportsPath` fails, fall back to `Qml2ImportsPath` for compatibility with Qt5.\n\nSuggested implementation:\n```python\ntry:\n    copy_qt_files(finder, name, \"QmlImportsPath\", \"*\")\nexcept KeyError:\n    # Fall back to Qml2ImportsPath for Qt5 compatibility\n    copy_qt_files(finder, name, \"Qml2ImportsPath\", \"*\")\n```\n\n**Environment Details:**\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Dependencies</b></summary>\n\n```\nvaik v0.1.0\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 attrs v25.4.0\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 pymodbus v3.6.9\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 pyqt5 v5.15.11\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 pyqt5-qt5 v5.15.2\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 pyqt5-sip v12.17.2\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 pyserial v3.5\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 pyserial-asyncio v0.6\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 pyserial v3.5\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 qasync v0.28.0\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 cx-freeze v8.5.3 (group: dev)\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 freeze-core v0.5.0\n\u2502   \u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 cabarchive v0.2.4\n\u2502   \u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 filelock v3.20.3\n\u2502   \u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 striprtf v0.0.29\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 lief v0.17.1\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 packaging v25.0\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 python-msilib v0.5.0\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 setuptools v80.9.0\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 openpyxl v3.1.5 (group: dev)\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 et-xmlfile v2.0.0\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 typer v0.21.1 (group: dev)\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 click v8.3.1\n    \u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 colorama v0.4.6\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 rich v14.2.0\n    \u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 markdown-it-py v4.0.0\n    \u2502   \u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 mdurl v0.1.2\n    \u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 pygments v2.19.2\n    \u251c\u2500\u2500 shellingham v1.5.4\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 typing-extensions v4.15.0\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Error Traceback</b></summary>\n\n```\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\release.py\", line 177, in <module>\n    main(console_args)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\release.py\", line 158, in main\n    setup(\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\__init__.py\", line 70, in setup\n    return setuptools.setup(**attrs)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\setuptools\\__init__.py\", line 115, in setup\n    return distutils.core.setup(**attrs)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\setuptools\\_distutils\\core.py\", line 186, in setup\n    return run_commands(dist)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\setuptools\\_distutils\\core.py\", line 202, in run_commands\n    dist.run_commands()\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\setuptools\\_distutils\\dist.py\", line 1002, in run_commands\n    self.run_command(cmd)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\setuptools\\dist.py\", line 1102, in run_command\n    super().run_command(command)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\setuptools\\_distutils\\dist.py\", line 1021, in run_command\n    cmd_obj.run()\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\command\\build_exe.py\", line 331, in run\n    freezer.freeze()\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\freezer.py\", line 822, in freeze\n    self._freeze_executable(executable)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\freezer.py\", line 361, in _freeze_executable\n    finder.include_file_as_module(exe.main_script, exe.main_module_name)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 724, in include_file_as_module\n    module = self._load_module_from_file(name, path, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 542, in _load_module_from_file\n    self._load_module_code(module, loader, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 512, in _load_module_code\n    self._scan_code(module, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 622, in _scan_code\n    imported_module = self._import_module(\n        name, deferred_imports, module, relative_import_index\n    )\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 260, in _import_module\n    module = self._internal_import_module(name, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 347, in _internal_import_module\n    module = self._load_module(\n        name, path, deferred_imports, parent_module\n    )\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 449, in _load_module\n    self._load_module_code(module, loader, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 512, in _load_module_code\n    self._scan_code(module, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 622, in _scan_code\n    imported_module = self._import_module(\n        name, deferred_imports, module, relative_import_index\n    )\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 260, in _import_module\n    module = self._internal_import_module(name, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 347, in _internal_import_module\n    module = self._load_module(\n        name, path, deferred_imports, parent_module\n    )\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 449, in _load_module\n    self._load_module_code(module, loader, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 512, in _load_module_code\n    self._scan_code(module, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 622, in _scan_code\n    imported_module = self._import_module(\n        name, deferred_imports, module, relative_import_index\n    )\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 260, in _import_module\n    module = self._internal_import_module(name, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 347, in _internal_import_module\n    module = self._load_module(\n        name, path, deferred_imports, parent_module\n    )\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 449, in _load_module\n    self._load_module_code(module, loader, deferred_imports)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 488, in _load_module_code\n    module.hook(self)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\hooks\\qthooks.py\", line 287, in qt_qtqml\n    copy_qt_files(finder, name, \"QmlImportsPath\", \"*\")\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\hooks\\qthooks.py\", line 159, in copy_qt_files\n    for source_path, target_path in _get_qt_files(name, variable, arg):\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\hooks\\qthooks.py\", line 135, in _get_qt_files\n    source_path, target_path = get_qt_paths(name, variable)\n  File \"E:\\code\\vaik\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\hooks\\qthooks.py\", line 127, in get_qt_paths\n    source_path, target_path = libraryinfo_paths[variable]\nKeyError: 'QmlImportsPath'\n```\n\n</details>\n\n**System Information:**\n- OS: Windows 10 Pro 22H2 Build 19045.4123\n- Python: 3.13.7\n- cx_Freeze: 8.5.3\n- PyQt5: 5.15.11\n\n**References:**\n- Qt5.15 documentation for `QLibraryInfo::LibraryPath`: https://doc.qt.io/archives/qt-5.15/qlibraryinfo.html#LibraryPath-enum\n- Qt6 documentation showing `Qml2ImportsPath` as deprecated: https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qlibraryinfo.html#LibraryPath-enum\n", "hints_text": "@realrushen Can you create a PR with your suggested implementation?\nCould you clarify which environment PyQt5 works with Python 3.13? Conda?\n\n", "all_hints_text": "@realrushen Can you create a PR with your suggested implementation?\nCould you clarify which environment PyQt5 works with Python 3.13? Conda?\n@marcelotduarte Thank you for the response.\n\nTo clarify your question about the environment:\n\nI am using uv to manage the virtual environment and dependencies for this project, not Conda.\n\nI have verified that the proposed fix works correctly on Windows 10 (as described in the original issue) and Astra Linux (based on Ubuntu), kernel 5.4.0-54-generic x86_64 GNU/Linux.\n\nThe KeyError: 'QmlImportsPath' occurred consistently on both platforms when freezing a PyQt5 application, and the try...except fallback to Qml2ImportsPath resolved it in both cases without breaking Qt6 functionality.\n[Release 8.6.0](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/releases/tag/8.6.0) is out!\n[Documentation](https://cx-freeze.readthedocs.io)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/a4dc3edaf6714f9ec78a18e39c4b4d3971366d25"], "created_at": "2026-01-14T16:20:31Z"}
{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3246, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3246", "issue_numbers": [3244], "base_commit": "909a50ecf4a2a3955e31b046cc5aef713bf59c27", "patch": "diff --git a/cx_Freeze/hooks/__init__.py b/cx_Freeze/hooks/__init__.py\nindex 296a93099..c9c0de6c7 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/hooks/__init__.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/hooks/__init__.py\n@@ -415,14 +415,6 @@ def load_pycountry(finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n     module.in_file_system = 1\n \n \n-def load_pycparser(finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"These files are missing which causes\n-    permission denied issues on windows when they are regenerated.\n-    \"\"\"\n-    finder.include_module(\"pycparser.lextab\")\n-    finder.include_module(\"pycparser.yacctab\")\n-\n-\n def load_pyodbc(finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n     \"\"\"The pyodbc module implicitly imports others modules;\n     make sure this happens.\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pycparser_.py b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pycparser_.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 000000000..f3021686d\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pycparser_.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+\"\"\"A collection of functions which are triggered automatically by finder when\n+pycparser package is included.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+from typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n+\n+from cx_Freeze.module import Module, ModuleHook\n+\n+if TYPE_CHECKING:\n+    from cx_Freeze.finder import ModuleFinder\n+\n+\n+__all__ = [\"Hook\"]\n+\n+\n+class Hook(ModuleHook):\n+    \"\"\"The Hook class for pycparser.\n+\n+    Supported versions: 2.21 to 3.0.\n+    \"\"\"\n+\n+    def pycparser(self, finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n+        \"\"\"Avoid permission denied issues on windows, using pycparser < 3.0.\n+\n+        When lextab and yacctab modules are regenerated.\n+        \"\"\"\n+        distribution = module.distribution\n+        if distribution and distribution.version < (3,):\n+            finder.include_module(\"pycparser.lextab\")\n+            finder.include_module(\"pycparser.yacctab\")\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py\nindex 6ac1b51a3..f6bca3cac 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py\n@@ -31,7 +31,8 @@ def pydantic(self, finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n                 \"PydanticUserError\",\n             ]\n         )\n-        if module.distribution.version < (2,):\n+        distribution = module.distribution\n+        if distribution and distribution.version < (2,):\n             finder.include_module(\"colorsys\")\n             finder.include_module(\"datetime\")\n             finder.include_module(\"decimal\")\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/hooks/test_pycparser.py b/tests/hooks/test_pycparser.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 000000000..1965dd34a\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/hooks/test_pycparser.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,74 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for hooks of pycparser.\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+TIMEOUT = 15\n+\n+zip_packages = pytest.mark.parametrize(\n+    \"zip_packages\", [False, True], ids=[\"\", \"zip_packages\"]\n+)\n+\n+SOURCE_TEST_PYCPARSER = \"\"\"\n+test_pycparser.py\n+    import pycparser\n+\n+    print(\"Hello from cx_Freeze\")\n+    print(\"pycparser version\", pycparser.__version__)\n+\n+    text = r'''\n+    void func(void)\n+    {\n+      x = 1;\n+    }\n+    '''\n+\n+    if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n+        parser = pycparser.c_parser.CParser()\n+        ast = parser.parse(text)\n+        print(\"Before:\")\n+        ast.show(offset=2)\n+\n+        assign = ast.ext[0].body.block_items[0]\n+        assign.lvalue.name = \"y\"\n+        assign.rvalue.value = 2\n+\n+        print(\"After:\")\n+        ast.show(offset=2)\n+pyproject.toml\n+    [project]\n+    name = \"test_pycparser\"\n+    version = \"0.1.2.3\"\n+    dependencies = [\n+        \"pycparser<3.0;python_version < '3.12'\",\n+        \"pycparser>=3.0;python_version >= '3.12'\",\n+    ]\n+\n+    [tool.cxfreeze]\n+    executables = [\"test_pycparser.py\"]\n+\n+    [tool.cxfreeze.build_exe]\n+    include_msvcr = true\n+    excludes = [\"tkinter\", \"unittest\"]\n+    silent = true\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+\n+@pytest.mark.venv\n+@zip_packages\n+def test_pycparser(tmp_package, zip_packages: bool) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test if pycparser hook is working correctly.\"\"\"\n+    tmp_package.create(SOURCE_TEST_PYCPARSER)\n+    if zip_packages:\n+        pyproject = tmp_package.path / \"pyproject.toml\"\n+        buf = pyproject.read_bytes().decode().splitlines()\n+        buf += ['zip_include_packages = \"*\"', 'zip_exclude_packages = \"\"']\n+        pyproject.write_bytes(\"\\n\".join(buf).encode(\"utf_8\"))\n+    tmp_package.freeze()\n+    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"test_pycparser\")\n+    assert executable.is_file()\n+    result = tmp_package.run(executable, timeout=TIMEOUT)\n+    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\n+        [\"Hello from cx_Freeze\", \"pycparser version *\"]\n+    )\n", "problem_statement": "Frozen applications fail to import `pycparser==3.0` correctly\n**Prerequisite**\n\n- [x] Make sure no duplicated issue has already been reported. You should look for closed issues, too.\n- [x] Make sure you are not asking us to help to solve your specific issue. GitHub issues are opened mainly for development purposes. If you want to ask someone to help to solve your problem, go to some community site like StackOverflow, etc.\n- [x] Make sure your problem is not derived from packaging (e.g. Homebrew).\n\n**Describe the bug**\nA frozen application that imports `pycparser==3.0` will fail to import the module with a traceback as shown below.\n\n```\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"C:\\work\\QA\\ThirdParty\\cx_Freeze\\freeze_clr\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\freeze_core\\initscripts\\__startup__.py\", line 137, in run\n    module_init.run(f\"__main__{name}\")\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"C:\\work\\QA\\ThirdParty\\cx_Freeze\\freeze_clr\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\freeze_core\\initscripts\\console.py\", line 27, in run\n    exec(code, main_globals)\n    ~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"import_pycparser.py\", line 1, in <module>\n    import pycparser\n  File \"C:\\work\\QA\\ThirdParty\\cx_Freeze\\freeze_clr\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\pycparser\\__init__.py\", line 16, in <module>\n    from . import c_parser\nImportError: cannot import name 'c_parser' from partially initialized module 'pycparser' (most likely due to a circular import) (C:\\work\\QA\\ThirdParty\\cx_Freeze\\freeze_clr\\build\\exe.win-amd64-3.13\\lib\\pycparser\\__init__.pyc)\n```\n**To Reproduce**\n1. In a fresh virtual environment, install pycparser and cx_Freeze:\n   `pip install pycparser==3.0 cx_Freeze==8.5.3`\n2. Freeze and run the following one line script using `cxfreeze --script script.py`:\n   `import pycparser`\n\n**Expected behavior**\nNo output from the script as it only imports a module.\n\n**Screenshots**\nN/A\n\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\n\n- Platform information (e.g. Ubuntu Linux 22.04): Windows 11 24H2\n- OS architecture (e.g. amd64): amd64\n- cx_Freeze version [e.g. 6.11]: 8.5.3\n- Python version [e.g. 3.10]: 3.10 through 3.13\n\n**Additional context**\n- Downgrading to `pycparser<3` results in the expected behavior.\n- The main branch of cx_Freeze as of commit a82c76e067205713dbe477ee2595ef8adcca5980 also exhibits the same behavior.\n\n", "hints_text": "Corrected name of package: ~pycparsing~ pycparser.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Corrected name of package: ~pycparsing~ pycparser.\nYou can test the PR with:\n`pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.3.3246.dev1769224632\"`\nUsing uv:\n`uv pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.5.3.3246.dev1769224632\" --index-strategy unsafe-best-match`\n\nI had the same problem when using pythonnet. The new release fixed it.\nThank you very much\n[Release 8.6.0](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/releases/tag/8.6.0) is out!\n[Documentation](https://cx-freeze.readthedocs.io)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/67b0b0a7bdc77e0dbc856a4631470d1302b47468"], "created_at": "2026-01-24T03:17:09Z"}
{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3272, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3272", "issue_numbers": [3271], "base_commit": "ed10d535124b26c0192e8e007c0a19d062f9db77", "patch": "diff --git a/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py\nindex f6bca3cac..94c102898 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py\n@@ -50,7 +50,7 @@ def pydantic__internal__core_utils(\n         self, _finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module\n     ) -> None:\n         \"\"\"Exclude optional modules.\"\"\"\n-        module.exclude_names.add(\"rich\")\n+        module.exclude_names.update([\"rich\", \"rich.console\", \"rich.pretty\"])\n \n     def pydantic__internal__typing_extra(\n         self, _finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/module.py b/cx_Freeze/module.py\nindex dc926a85f..0134f0307 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/module.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/module.py\n@@ -3,6 +3,7 @@\n from __future__ import annotations\n \n import ast\n+import re\n import socket\n from contextlib import suppress\n from datetime import datetime, timezone\n@@ -178,12 +179,14 @@ def requires(self) -> list[str]:\n         return package_names\n \n     @property\n-    def version(self) -> tuple[int, ...] | str | None:\n+    def version(self) -> tuple[int, ...]:\n         \"\"\"Return the 'Version' metadata for the distribution package.\"\"\"\n-        value = super().version\n-        with suppress(ValueError):\n-            value = tuple(map(int, value.split(\".\")))\n-        return value\n+        version_separators = re.compile(r\"[\\._-]\")\n+        version_value = super().version or \"\"\n+        return tuple(\n+            part.lower() if not part.isdigit() else int(part)\n+            for part in version_separators.split(version_value)\n+        )\n \n \n class Module:\ndiff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml\nindex 6e4dd5661..a7c19083c 100644\n--- a/pyproject.toml\n+++ b/pyproject.toml\n@@ -278,7 +278,6 @@ typing-modules = [\"cx_Freeze._typing\"]\n [tool.ruff.lint.per-file-ignores]\n \"cx_Freeze/command/_pydialog.py\" = [\"ERA001\"]\n \"cx_Freeze/command/bdist_msi.py\" = [\"ERA001\"]\n-\"samples/pydantic/test_pydantic.py\" = [\"E501\"]\n \"samples/*\" = [\"D1\"]\n \"tests/*\" = [\"S101\"]\n \ndiff --git a/samples/pydantic/setup.py b/samples/pydantic/setup.py\ndeleted file mode 100644\nindex a0e2a056b..000000000\n--- a/samples/pydantic/setup.py\n+++ /dev/null\n@@ -1,16 +0,0 @@\n-\"\"\"A setup script to create a single executable.\"\"\"\n-\n-#\n-# Run the build process by running the command 'python setup.py build'\n-#\n-# If everything works well you should find a subdirectory in the build\n-# subdirectory that contains the files needed to run the script without Python\n-\n-from cx_Freeze import setup\n-\n-setup(\n-    name=\"test_pydantic\",\n-    version=\"0.1\",\n-    description=\"Test pydantic\",\n-    executables=[\"test_pydantic.py\"],\n-)\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/samples/pydantic/test_pydantic.py b/samples/pydantic/test_pydantic.py\ndeleted file mode 100644\nindex 7e2ec7613..000000000\n--- a/samples/pydantic/test_pydantic.py\n+++ /dev/null\n@@ -1,25 +0,0 @@\n-\"\"\"A simple example.\"\"\"\n-\n-# https://github.com/pydantic/pydantic?tab=readme-ov-file#a-simple-example\n-from datetime import datetime\n-\n-from pydantic import BaseModel\n-\n-\n-class User(BaseModel):\n-    id: int\n-    name: str = \"John Doe\"\n-    signup_ts: datetime | None = None\n-    friends: list[int] = []\n-\n-\n-external_data = {\n-    \"id\": \"123\",\n-    \"signup_ts\": \"2017-06-01 12:22\",\n-    \"friends\": [1, \"2\", b\"3\"],\n-}\n-user = User(**external_data)\n-print(user)\n-# > User id=123 name='John Doe' signup_ts=datetime.datetime(2017, 6, 1, 12, 22) friends=[1, 2, 3]\n-print(user.id)\n-# > 123\ndiff --git a/tests/hooks/test_pydantic.py b/tests/hooks/test_pydantic.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 000000000..c47ec0da8\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/hooks/test_pydantic.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,88 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for hooks of pydantic.\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import sys\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+from cx_Freeze._compat import ABI_THREAD\n+\n+zip_packages = pytest.mark.parametrize(\n+    \"zip_packages\", [False, True], ids=[\"\", \"zip_packages\"]\n+)\n+\n+SOURCE_TEST_PYDANTIC = \"\"\"\n+test_pydantic.py\n+    import pydantic\n+\n+    print(\"Hello from cx_Freeze\")\n+    print(\"pydantic version\", pydantic.__version__)\n+\n+    # https://github.com/pydantic/pydantic?tab=readme-ov-file#a-simple-example\n+    from datetime import datetime\n+\n+    from pydantic import BaseModel\n+\n+\n+    class User(BaseModel):\n+        id: int\n+        name: str = \"John Doe\"\n+        signup_ts: datetime | None = None\n+        friends: list[int] = []\n+\n+\n+    external_data = {\n+        \"id\": \"123\",\n+        \"signup_ts\": \"2017-06-01 12:22\",\n+        \"friends\": [1, \"2\", b\"3\"],\n+    }\n+    user = User(**external_data)\n+    print(user)\n+    print(user.id)\n+pyproject.toml\n+    [project]\n+    name = \"test_pydantic\"\n+    version = \"0.1.2.3\"\n+    dependencies = [\"pydantic==2.13.0b2\"]\n+\n+    [tool.cxfreeze]\n+    executables = [\"test_pydantic.py\"]\n+\n+    [tool.cxfreeze.build_exe]\n+    include_msvcr = true\n+    excludes = [\"tkinter\", \"unittest\"]\n+    silent = true\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+\n+@pytest.mark.xfail(\n+    sys.version_info[:2] == (3, 13) and ABI_THREAD == \"t\",\n+    raises=ModuleNotFoundError,\n+    reason=\"pydantic_core does not support Python 3.13t\",\n+    strict=True,\n+)\n+@pytest.mark.venv\n+@zip_packages\n+def test_pydantic(tmp_package, zip_packages: bool) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test if pydantic hook is working correctly.\"\"\"\n+    tmp_package.create(SOURCE_TEST_PYDANTIC)\n+    if zip_packages:\n+        pyproject = tmp_package.path / \"pyproject.toml\"\n+        buf = pyproject.read_bytes().decode().splitlines()\n+        buf += ['zip_include_packages = \"*\"', 'zip_exclude_packages = \"\"']\n+        pyproject.write_bytes(\"\\n\".join(buf).encode(\"utf_8\"))\n+    tmp_package.freeze()\n+    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"test_pydantic\")\n+    assert executable.is_file()\n+    result = tmp_package.run(executable)\n+    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\n+        [\n+            \"Hello from cx_Freeze\",\n+            \"pydantic version *\",\n+            \"id=123 name='John Doe' \"\n+            \"signup_ts=datetime.datetime(2017, 6, 1, 12, 22) \"\n+            \"friends=[1, 2, 3]\",\n+            \"123\",\n+        ]\n+    )\ndiff --git a/tests/hooks/test_qt.py b/tests/hooks/test_qt.py\nindex 9cd8bcc78..ed9cc9248 100644\n--- a/tests/hooks/test_qt.py\n+++ b/tests/hooks/test_qt.py\n@@ -91,8 +91,6 @@ def test_qt(tmp_package, qt_impl) -> None:\n         if qt_impl == \"PySide2\":\n             if IS_MACOS:\n                 pytest.skip(\"PySide2 does not support macOS\")\n-            if IS_MINGW:\n-                pytest.skip(\"PySide2 failing in MSYS2\")\n             if not IS_MINGW and sys.version_info[:2] >= (3, 11):\n                 pytest.skip(\"PySide2 does not support Python 3.11+\")\n         if (\n", "problem_statement": "Using Pydantic module intermediary version will crash cx_Freeze\n\n**Describe the bug**\nUsing Pydantic module with version v2.13.0b2 instead of the current v2.12.5\n\n**To Reproduce**\nTry to freeze any project\n\n**Expected behavior**\nProject is frozen without errors\n\n**Additional context**\nAdd any other context about the problem here.\n```\nError:\nFile \"D:\\Dev\\.venv_3.14\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\hooks\\_pydantic_.py\", line 35, in pydantic\n    if module.distribution.version < (2,):\n       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nTypeError: '<' not supported between instances of 'str' and 'tuple'\n```\n\n**Fix**\nReplace line:\n```if module.distribution.version < (2,):```\nwith something like this:\n```\nmod_version = module.distribution.version\nif instance(mod_version, str):\n\tversion_ok = int(module.distribution.version.split('.')[0]) < 2\nelse:\n\tversion_ok = module.distribution.version < (2,)\n\nif version_ok:\n\t# code\n```\n\nOr \n\n```\nfrom packaging.version import Version\n\nmod_version = module.distribution.version\n\n# If it's a tuple like (2, 12, 5, ), convert it to a string \"2.12.5\"\nif isinstance(mod_version , tuple):\n    mod_version = \".\".join(map(str, mod_version ))\n\nversion_ok = Version(mod_version ) < Version(\"2.0\")\n\nif version_ok:\n\t# code\n```\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "How to install this beta version?\nWhat is the version of cx_Freeze you are using? \nI assume you're using an older version than the current one, which is 8.6.0, because line 35 is different in that version:\nhttps://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/blob/main/cx_Freeze/hooks/_pydantic_.py#L35\nIf that's the case, could you try the latest version?\nEDIT: \nYou can ignore these questions. See the next comment.\n\nI made a patch that corrects the version so that it always returns a tuple.\n\nYou can test the PR with:\n`pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.6.1.dev1772600937\"`\nUsing uv:\n`uv pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.6.1.dev1772600937\" --index-strategy unsafe-best-match`\n\nHi,\nThe Pydantic module with version v2.13.0b2 was the one suggested inside PyCharm. It continuously pushes for the latest packages even if they are not public releases (it may be a setting somewhere to control this behavior).\n\nI was using Cx Freeze latest version, thought that the problem was in the latest changes and reverted to the previous version. Same story, then I investigated and found the fix reported above. But it was easy for me to just back the Pydantic to the current (numeric version).\n\nI thought to report here the finding, it is the least I could do, maybe it will help others.\n\n<img width=\"2156\" height=\"1424\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7aa7b8e4-643d-4314-a1e3-3bbda10a3eac\" />\n\n\nI tested the PR with:\n`pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.6.1.dev1772600937\"`\n\nAnd the issue is fixed.\nTHANK YOU!\nYes, of course you helped. One less bug. ;-)\n[Release 8.6.1](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/releases/tag/8.6.1) is out!\n[Documentation](https://cx-freeze.readthedocs.io)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/f15e88d6d197604263dac3e9f0176cbc3e7da6bf", "https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/938a0515bd4396a1de45e83d315129263610384c"], "created_at": "2026-03-04T05:08:55Z"}
{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3283, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3283", "issue_numbers": [3282], "base_commit": "f7072cc798b80c58d9aea757e470a4c48e81eda3", "patch": "diff --git a/.github/workflows/dependency-review.yml b/.github/workflows/dependency-review.yml\nindex 4367c6f15..f56388863 100644\n--- a/.github/workflows/dependency-review.yml\n+++ b/.github/workflows/dependency-review.yml\n@@ -24,4 +24,4 @@ jobs:\n       - name: Checkout Repository\n         uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd # v6.0.2\n       - name: Dependency Review\n-        uses: actions/dependency-review-action@3c4e3dcb1aa7874d2c16be7d79418e9b7efd6261 # v4.8.2\n+        uses: actions/dependency-review-action@2031cfc080254a8a887f58cffee85186f0e49e48 # v4.9.0\ndiff --git a/.pre-commit-config.yaml b/.pre-commit-config.yaml\nindex 964e91981..491662293 100644\n--- a/.pre-commit-config.yaml\n+++ b/.pre-commit-config.yaml\n@@ -39,7 +39,7 @@ repos:\n           - validate-pyproject-schema-store[all]>=2025.11.14\n \n   - repo: https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit\n-    rev: v0.15.6\n+    rev: v0.15.7\n     hooks:\n       - id: ruff-check\n         args: [\"--fix\", \"--show-fixes\"]\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/hooks/_ssl_.py b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_ssl_.py\nindex ab7a2b69a..0abd68042 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/hooks/_ssl_.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_ssl_.py\n@@ -60,7 +60,7 @@ def ssl(self, finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n                 import os as _os\n                 import sys as _sys\n                 _cert_file = _os.environ.get(\"SSL_CERT_FILE\")\n-                if _cert_file is None or not _os.path.exists(cert_file):\n+                if _cert_file is None or not _os.path.exists(_cert_file):\n                     _prefix = _sys.prefix\n                     if _sys.platform == \"darwin\":\n                         _mac_prefix = _os.path.join(\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/hooks/test_stdlib.py b/tests/hooks/test_stdlib.py\nindex abe2ffc42..ef69acbb3 100644\n--- a/tests/hooks/test_stdlib.py\n+++ b/tests/hooks/test_stdlib.py\n@@ -169,9 +169,17 @@ def test_sqlite_ext(tmp_package, zip_packages: bool) -> None:\n \"\"\"\n \n \n+@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n+    \"use_os_cert_file\", [False, True], ids=[\"\", \"SSL_CERT_FILE\"]\n+)\n @mac_extra_test\n @zip_packages\n-def test_ssl(tmp_package, zip_packages: bool, mac_extra_test: bool) -> None:\n+def test_ssl(\n+    tmp_package,\n+    zip_packages: bool,\n+    mac_extra_test: bool,\n+    use_os_cert_file: bool,\n+) -> None:\n     \"\"\"Test that the ssl is working correctly.\"\"\"\n     tmp_package.create(SOURCE_TEST_SSL)\n     if zip_packages:\n@@ -190,7 +198,15 @@ def test_ssl(tmp_package, zip_packages: bool, mac_extra_test: bool) -> None:\n         tmp_package.freeze()\n         executable = tmp_package.executable(\"test_ssl\")\n     assert executable.is_file()\n-    result = tmp_package.run(executable)\n+    env = os.environ.copy()\n+    if use_os_cert_file:\n+        ssl_paths = __import__(\"ssl\").get_default_verify_paths()\n+        cert_file = ssl_paths.cafile\n+        if cert_file and not os.path.exists(cert_file):\n+            cert_file = ssl_paths.openssl_cafile\n+        if cert_file and os.path.exists(cert_file):\n+            env[\"SSL_CERT_FILE\"] = cert_file\n+    result = tmp_package.run(executable, env=env)\n     result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\n         [\n             \"Hello from cx_Freeze\",\n", "problem_statement": "Importing ssl module (using SSL_CERT_FILE environ) fails with NameError\n**Describe the bug**\nImporting Python's ssl module in a frozen program results in a NameError exception.\n```\nNameError: name 'cert_file' is not defined \n```\n\n**To Reproduce**\n`import ssl` in a program.\n\n**Expected behavior**\nModule is successfully imported.\n\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\n\n- Platform information (e.g. Ubuntu Linux 22.04): macOS 15\n- OS architecture (e.g. amd64): x86_64\n- cx_Freeze version [e.g. 6.11]: 8.6.1\n- Python version [e.g. 3.10]: 3.14\n\n**Additional context**\nIt looks like a recent issue in commit https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/199020cd65d80cc35687310f7e8ba37595e323bf. `cert_file` should be `_cert_file` here:\n```\nif _cert_file is None or not _os.path.exists(cert_file):\n```\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Thanks!\n[Release 8.6.2](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/releases/tag/8.6.2) is out!\n[Documentation](https://cx-freeze.readthedocs.io)\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/8f581cc14aecf2dafe599cd14c4fc543060e3ddf", "https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/87fe1d88b331006b43248b72a6fa35735668f157"], "created_at": "2026-03-19T16:37:36Z"}
{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3287, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3287", "issue_numbers": [3286], "base_commit": "3464e6ba34f4d0d33ad9fae23f0d1f272912ccaa", "patch": "diff --git a/cx_Freeze/hooks/__init__.py b/cx_Freeze/hooks/__init__.py\nindex 50900e3b7..c3df1f20e 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/hooks/__init__.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/hooks/__init__.py\n@@ -102,18 +102,6 @@ def load_cffi_cparser(finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n         module.ignore_names.add(\"cffi._pycparser\")\n \n \n-def load_charset_normalizer(finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"The charset_normalizer package.\"\"\"\n-    finder.exclude_module(\"charset_normalizer.cli\")\n-\n-\n-def load_charset_normalizer_md(finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n-    \"\"\"The charset_normalizer package implicitly imports a extension module.\"\"\"\n-    mypyc = module.file.parent / (\"md__mypyc\" + \"\".join(module.file.suffixes))\n-    if mypyc.exists():\n-        finder.include_module(\"charset_normalizer.md__mypyc\")\n-\n-\n def load_collections(finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n     \"\"\"Sets the alias for collections.abc.\"\"\"\n     try:\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/hooks/_charset_normalizer_.py b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_charset_normalizer_.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 000000000..9ee98f570\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/hooks/_charset_normalizer_.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+\"\"\"A collection of functions which are triggered automatically by finder when\n+charset_normalizer package is included.\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+from contextlib import suppress\n+from typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n+\n+from cx_Freeze.module import Module, ModuleHook\n+\n+if TYPE_CHECKING:\n+    from cx_Freeze.finder import ModuleFinder\n+\n+\n+__all__ = [\"Hook\"]\n+\n+\n+class Hook(ModuleHook):\n+    \"\"\"The Hook class for charset_normalizer.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def charset_normalizer(self, finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module) -> None:\n+        \"\"\"The charset_normalizer package.\"\"\"\n+        finder.exclude_module(f\"{module.name}.cli\")\n+\n+    def charset_normalizer_md(\n+        self, finder: ModuleFinder, module: Module\n+    ) -> None:\n+        \"\"\"The charset_normalizer.md implicitly imports an extension module.\"\"\"\n+        with suppress(ImportError):\n+            # charset_normalizer 3.0 to 3.4.4\n+            finder.include_module(\"charset_normalizer.md__mypyc\")\n+        # charset_normalizer 3.4.5+\n+        suffix = \"\".join(module.file.suffixes)\n+        for mypyc in module.file.parent.parent.glob(f\"*__mypyc{suffix}\"):\n+            if mypyc.exists():\n+                finder.include_module(f\"{mypyc.name.split('.')[0]}\")\n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/hooks/test_charset_normalizer.py b/tests/hooks/test_charset_normalizer.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 000000000..be3fc083e\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/hooks/test_charset_normalizer.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,54 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for hooks of charset_normalizer.\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+TIMEOUT = 15\n+\n+zip_packages = pytest.mark.parametrize(\n+    \"zip_packages\", [False, True], ids=[\"\", \"zip_packages\"]\n+)\n+\n+SOURCE_TEST_CHARSET_NORMALIZER = \"\"\"\n+test_charset_normalizer.py\n+    import charset_normalizer\n+\n+    print(\"Hello from cx_Freeze\")\n+    print(\"charset_normalizer version\", charset_normalizer.__version__)\n+pyproject.toml\n+    [project]\n+    name = \"test_charset_normalizer\"\n+    version = \"0.1.2.3\"\n+    dependencies = [\n+        \"charset_normalizer<3.0;python_version < '3.12'\",\n+        \"charset_normalizer>=3.0;python_version >= '3.12'\",\n+    ]\n+\n+    [tool.cxfreeze]\n+    executables = [\"test_charset_normalizer.py\"]\n+\n+    [tool.cxfreeze.build_exe]\n+    include_msvcr = true\n+    excludes = [\"tkinter\", \"unittest\"]\n+    silent = true\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+\n+@pytest.mark.venv\n+@zip_packages\n+def test_charset_normalizer(tmp_package, zip_packages: bool) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test if charset_normalizer hook is working correctly.\"\"\"\n+    tmp_package.create(SOURCE_TEST_CHARSET_NORMALIZER)\n+    if zip_packages:\n+        pyproject = tmp_package.path / \"pyproject.toml\"\n+        buf = pyproject.read_bytes().decode().splitlines()\n+        buf += ['zip_include_packages = \"*\"', 'zip_exclude_packages = \"\"']\n+        pyproject.write_bytes(\"\\n\".join(buf).encode(\"utf_8\"))\n+    tmp_package.freeze()\n+    executable = tmp_package.executable(\"test_charset_normalizer\")\n+    assert executable.is_file()\n+    result = tmp_package.run(executable, timeout=TIMEOUT)\n+    result.stdout.fnmatch_lines(\n+        [\"Hello from cx_Freeze\", \"charset_normalizer version *\"]\n+    )\n", "problem_statement": "charset-normalizer 3.4.5+  fails to load\n**Prerequisite**\n\n- Make sure no duplicated issue has already been reported. You should look for closed issues, too.\n- Make sure you are not asking us to help to solve your specific issue. GitHub issues are opened mainly for development purposes. If you want to ask someone to help to solve your problem, go to some community site like StackOverflow, etc.\n- Make sure your problem is not derived from packaging (e.g. Homebrew).\n\n**Describe the bug**\ni getting some reports that a binary i build with cx_freeze showing a warning message from requests:\n```\nC:\\hostedtoolcache\\windows\\Python\\3.13.12\\x86\\Lib\\site-packages\\requests\\__init__.py:86: RequestsDependencyWarning: Unable to find acceptable character detection dependency (chardet or charset_normalizer).\n```\nit turns out it failed to load charset_normalizer 3.4.5+.\n\ndoing some googling i found this issue https://github.com/jawah/charset_normalizer/issues/714  \nif i add `81d243bd2c585b0f4821__mypyc` in the include \n```toml\n[tool.cxfreeze.build_exe]\nincludes = [\"81d243bd2c585b0f4821__mypyc\"]\n```\nit works without any issue with this change.\ni dont know if this  should be in a hook in cx_freeze or not.\nmaybe someone else find this issue and here is a fix for it :)\n\n**To Reproduce**\n```\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb cat script.py\nimport charset_normalizer\nprint(\"hello world\")\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb cat pyproject.toml\n[project]\nname = \"foo\"\nversion = \"0.1\"\ndescription = \"script\"\n\n[tool.cxfreeze]\nexecutables = [\n    {script = \"script.py\"}\n]\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb pip install charset_normalizer==3.4.5  cx_freeze\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb cxfreeze build\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb ./build/exe.linux-x86_64-3.12/script\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/home/johan/dev/cx_bug/lib/python3.12/site-packages/freeze_core/initscripts/__startup__.py\", line 137, in run\n    module_init.run(f\"__main__{name}\")\n  File \"/home/johan/dev/cx_bug/lib/python3.12/site-packages/freeze_core/initscripts/console.py\", line 27, in run\n    exec(code, main_globals)\n  File \"script.py\", line 1, in <module>\n    import charset_normalizer\n  File \"/home/johan/dev/cx_bug/lib/python3.12/site-packages/charset_normalizer/__init__.py\", line 26, in <module>\n    from .api import from_bytes, from_fp, from_path, is_binary\n  File \"/home/johan/dev/cx_bug/lib/python3.12/site-packages/charset_normalizer/api.py\", line 7, in <module>\n    from .cd import (\nModuleNotFoundError: No module named '81d243bd2c585b0f4821__mypyc'\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb cat pyproject.toml\n[project]\nname = \"foo\"\nversion = \"0.1\"\ndescription = \"script\"\n\n[tool.cxfreeze]\nexecutables = [\n    {script = \"script.py\"}\n]\n[tool.cxfreeze.build_exe]\nincludes = [\"81d243bd2c585b0f4821__mypyc\"]\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb cxfreeze build\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb ./build/exe.linux-x86_64-3.12/script\nhello world\n(cx_bug) fallen dev/cx_bug \u00bb\n```\n\n**Expected behavior**\ni expected to get a `Hello world` output\n\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\n\n- Platform information (e.g. Ubuntu Linux 22.04): Ubuntu 24.04 / Windows  11\n- OS architecture (e.g. amd64): amd64\n- cx_Freeze version [e.g. 6.11]: 8.6.2\n- Python version [e.g. 3.10]: 3.12.4  and 3.13. \n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "You can test the PR with:\n`pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.6.3.dev1774241229\"`\nUsing uv:\n`uv pip install --extra-index-url https://test.pypi.org/simple/ \"cx-Freeze==8.6.3.dev1774241229\" --index-strategy unsafe-best-match`\n\nIt works. Thank you for the fix \ud83d\ude00\n[Release 8.6.3](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/releases/tag/8.6.3) is out!\n[Documentation](https://cx-freeze.readthedocs.io)\n\nThank you for your contribution!\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/03911f8ab46a4c7bd31fe6b125198c06d55b20dc"], "created_at": "2026-03-23T02:04:01Z"}
{"repo": "marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze", "pull_number": 3306, "instance_id": "marcelotduarte__cx_Freeze-3306", "issue_numbers": [3305], "base_commit": "d86617c087460586c9ff5a9c66d75ca6c071f992", "patch": "diff --git a/cx_Freeze/finder.py b/cx_Freeze/finder.py\nindex 64e568818..d26188177 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/finder.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/finder.py\n@@ -3,15 +3,19 @@\n from __future__ import annotations\n \n import importlib.machinery\n+import inspect\n+import linecache\n import logging\n import os\n import sys\n+import traceback\n from contextlib import suppress\n from functools import cached_property\n from pathlib import Path, PurePath\n from pkgutil import resolve_name\n from sysconfig import get_config_var\n from tempfile import TemporaryDirectory\n+from types import FrameType, TracebackType\n from typing import TYPE_CHECKING\n \n from cx_Freeze._bytecode import (\n@@ -219,7 +223,7 @@ def _import_all_sub_modules(\n                 if sub_module is None:\n                     if sub_module_name not in self.excludes:\n                         msg = f\"No module named {sub_module_name!r}\"\n-                        raise ImportError(msg)\n+                        raise ImportError(msg, name=sub_module_name)\n                 else:\n                     module.global_names.add(name)\n                     if sub_module.path and recursive:\n@@ -298,7 +302,7 @@ def _import_module(\n         if module is None:\n             if caller is None:\n                 msg = f\"No module named {name!r}\"\n-                raise ImportError(msg)\n+                raise ImportError(msg, name=name)\n             self._missing_hook(caller, name)\n \n         return module\n@@ -467,22 +471,28 @@ def _load_module_code(\n                 module.code = loader.source_to_code(\n                     source_bytes, path, _optimize=self.optimize\n                 )\n-            except SyntaxError:\n-                logger.debug(\"Invalid syntax in [%s]\", name)\n-                msg = f\"Invalid syntax in {path}\"\n-                raise ImportError(msg, name=name) from None\n+            except SyntaxError as exc:\n+                module.error_exc = exc\n+                msg = f\"{exc.__class__.__name__}: {exc.msg}\"\n+                module.error_msg = msg\n+                logger.debug(\"%s in '%s' [%s]\", msg, path, name)\n+                return None\n         elif isinstance(loader, importlib.machinery.SourcelessFileLoader):\n             logger.debug(\"Adding module [%s] [BYTECODE]\", name)\n             # Load Python bytecode\n             module.code = loader.get_code(name)\n             if module.code is None:\n                 msg = f\"Bad magic number in {path}\"\n-                raise ImportError(msg, name=name)\n+                module.error_msg = msg\n+                logger.debug(\"%s in '%s' [%s]\", msg, path, name)\n+                return None\n         elif isinstance(loader, importlib.machinery.ExtensionFileLoader):\n             logger.debug(\"Adding module [%s] [EXTENSION]\", name)\n         else:\n             msg = f\"Unknown module loader in {path}\"\n-            raise ImportError(msg, name=name)  # noqa: TRY004\n+            module.error_msg = msg\n+            logger.debug(\"%s in '%s' [%s]\", msg, path, name)\n+            return None\n \n         # Run custom hook for the module\n         if module.hook:\n@@ -531,7 +541,7 @@ def _load_module_from_file(\n         loader: ExecutionLoader | None = None\n \n         ext = filename.suffix\n-        path = os.fspath(filename)\n+        path = os.path.abspath(filename)\n         if not ext or ext in importlib.machinery.SOURCE_SUFFIXES:\n             loader = importlib.machinery.SourceFileLoader(name, path)\n         elif ext in importlib.machinery.BYTECODE_SUFFIXES:\n@@ -540,7 +550,19 @@ def _load_module_from_file(\n             loader = importlib.machinery.ExtensionFileLoader(name, path)\n \n         module = self._add_module(name, filename=filename)\n-        self._load_module_code(module, loader, deferred_imports)\n+        if self._load_module_code(module, loader, deferred_imports) is None:\n+            exc: Exception = module.error_exc\n+            msg = f\"ImportError: Cannot import {path!r}\"\n+            msg += \" due to the previous error.\"\n+            if exc is not None:\n+                frame = fake_frame(path, exc.lineno)\n+                fake_tb = TracebackType(None, frame, exc.lineno, exc.offset)\n+                traceback.print_exception(\n+                    exc, value=exc, tb=fake_tb, chain=False\n+                )\n+            elif module.error_msg is not None:\n+                msg = f\"Error: {module.error_msg}\\n{msg}\"\n+            sys.exit(msg)\n         return module\n \n     def _missing_hook(self, caller: Module, module_name: str) -> None:\n@@ -810,3 +832,12 @@ def zip_include_files(\n         self.zip_includes.extend(\n             process_path_specs([(source_path, target_path)])\n         )\n+\n+\n+def fake_frame(filename: str, lineno: int) -> FrameType:\n+    linecache.updatecache(filename)\n+    res = {}\n+    source = (\"\\n\" * max(0, lineno - 1)) + \"f=inspect.currentframe()\"\n+    code = compile(source, filename, \"exec\")\n+    exec(code, {\"inspect\": inspect}, res)  # noqa:S102\n+    return res[\"f\"]\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/freezer.py b/cx_Freeze/freezer.py\nindex 29e247209..9897b0233 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/freezer.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/freezer.py\n@@ -799,7 +799,7 @@ def _write_modules(self) -> None:\n             finally:\n                 os.environ[\"PATH\"] = orig_path\n \n-        # put all files in file system or keep in zip file\n+        # put all files in the file system or keep them in a zip file\n         if self.zip_filename is None:\n             with ZipFile(filename) as outfile:\n                 outfile.extractall(target_lib_dir)\n@@ -861,7 +861,7 @@ def freeze(self) -> None:\n     def print_report(self) -> None:\n         \"\"\"Display report:\n         - list of modules and packages;\n-        - list of modules  that weren't found;\n+        - list of modules that weren't found;\n         - list of dependencies that weren't found.\n         \"\"\"\n         if self.silent < 1:\ndiff --git a/cx_Freeze/module.py b/cx_Freeze/module.py\nindex 0134f0307..8cdecb614 100644\n--- a/cx_Freeze/module.py\n+++ b/cx_Freeze/module.py\n@@ -208,6 +208,8 @@ def __init__(\n         self.code: CodeType | None = None\n         self.cache_path: Path | None = None\n         self.distribution: DistributionCache | None = None\n+        self.error_exc: Exception | None = None\n+        self.error_msg: str | None = None\n         self.hook: ModuleHook | Callable | None = None\n         self.lazy: bool = False\n \n", "test_patch": "diff --git a/tests/datatest.py b/tests/datatest.py\nindex 33cc154e3..59cc24663 100644\n--- a/tests/datatest.py\n+++ b/tests/datatest.py\n@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@\n \n from __future__ import annotations\n \n-# Each test description is a list of 5 items:\n+# Each test description is a list of 6 items:\n #\n # 1. a module name that will be imported by ModuleFinder\n # 1.1. to import a package, use 'package:' prefix, e.g, \"package:foo\"\n@@ -490,7 +490,7 @@ def ok():\n SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST = [\n     \"invalid_syntax\",\n     [\"invalid_syntax\"],\n-    [],\n+    [\"invalid_syntax\"],\n     [],\n     \"\"\"\\\n invalid_syntax.py\n@@ -499,6 +499,19 @@ def ok():\n     {},\n ]\n \n+SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST_1 = [\n+    \"invalid_syntax_1\",\n+    [\"invalid_syntax_1\"],\n+    [\"invalid_syntax_1\"],\n+    [],\n+    r\"\"\"\n+invalid_syntax_1.py\n+    folder = \"C:\\Temp\\New\"  # Correct is r\"C:\\Temp\\New\" or \"C:\\\\Temp\\\\New\"\n+    print(\"folder:\", folder)\n+\"\"\",\n+    {},\n+]\n+\n SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST_2 = [\n     \"a.module\",\n     [\"a\", \"a.module\", \"b\", \"b.module\"],\ndiff --git a/tests/test_executables.py b/tests/test_executables.py\nindex 00a22d9bc..4e623c33c 100644\n--- a/tests/test_executables.py\n+++ b/tests/test_executables.py\n@@ -494,6 +494,34 @@ def test_invalid_icon(tmp_package) -> None:\n     )\n \n \n+SOURCE_INVALID_SYNTAX = r\"\"\"\n+test_invalid_syntax.py\n+    folder = \"C:\\Temp\\New\"\n+    print(\"folder:\", folder)\n+pyproject.toml\n+    [project]\n+    name = \"hello\"\n+    version = \"0.1.2.3\"\n+    description = \"Sample cx_Freeze script\"\n+\n+    [[tool.cxfreeze.executables]]\n+    script = \"test_invalid_syntax.py\"\n+\n+    [tool.cxfreeze.build_exe]\n+    include_msvcr = true\n+    excludes = [\"tkinter\", \"unittest\"]\n+    silent_level = 1\n+\"\"\"\n+\n+\n+def test_invalid_syntax(tmp_package) -> None:\n+    \"\"\"Test with invalid syntax.\"\"\"\n+    tmp_package.create(SOURCE_INVALID_SYNTAX)\n+    result = tmp_package.freeze()\n+    # it is expected the following error\n+    result.stderr.fnmatch_lines(\"SyntaxError: *\")\n+\n+\n SOURCE_RENAME = \"\"\"\n test_0.py\n     print(\"Hello from cx_Freeze\")\ndiff --git a/tests/test_finder.py b/tests/test_finder.py\nindex 182264056..89d867aae 100644\n--- a/tests/test_finder.py\n+++ b/tests/test_finder.py\n@@ -45,6 +45,6 @@ def test_invalid_syntax(self, tmp_package, fix_module_finder) -> None:\n         \"\"\"Invalid syntax (e.g. Py2 only code) should not break freezing.\"\"\"\n         tmp_package.create(SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST[4])\n         fix_module_finder.path.insert(0, os.fspath(tmp_package.path))\n-        with pytest.raises(ImportError):\n-            # Threw SyntaxError before the bug was fixed\n-            fix_module_finder.include_module(\"invalid_syntax\")\n+        # Threw SyntaxError before the bug was fixed\n+        module = fix_module_finder.include_module(\"invalid_syntax\")\n+        assert module.error_msg == \"SyntaxError: invalid syntax\"\ndiff --git a/tests/test_modulefinder.py b/tests/test_modulefinder.py\nindex 536eb4ea3..7275e36bb 100644\n--- a/tests/test_modulefinder.py\n+++ b/tests/test_modulefinder.py\n@@ -37,20 +37,24 @@\n     SCAN_CODE_IMPORT_MODULE_TEST,\n     SCAN_CODE_TEST,\n     SUB_PACKAGE_TEST,\n+    SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST,\n+    SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST_1,\n     SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST_2,\n     ZIP_EXCLUDE_TEST,\n     ZIP_INCLUDE_TEST,\n )\n \n-# Each test description is a list of 5 items:\n+# Each test description is a list of 6 items:\n #\n # 1. a module name that will be imported by ModuleFinder\n+# 1.1. to import a package, use 'package:' prefix, e.g, \"package:foo\"\n # 2. a list of module names that ModuleFinder is required to find\n # 3. a list of module names that ModuleFinder should complain\n #    about because they are not found\n # 4. a list of module names that ModuleFinder should complain\n #    about because they MAY be not found\n # 5. a string specifying packages to create; the format is obvious imo.\n+# 6. a dictionary of ModuleFinder kwargs.\n #\n # Each package will be created in test_dir, and test_dir will be\n # removed after the tests again.\n@@ -60,11 +64,11 @@\n \n def _do_test(\n     test_dir,\n-    import_this,\n-    modules,\n-    missing,  # noqa: ARG001\n-    maybe_missing,  # noqa: ARG001\n-    source,\n+    import_this: str,\n+    modules: list[str],\n+    missing: list[str],\n+    maybe_missing: list[str],  # noqa: ARG001\n+    source: str,\n     report=False,\n     debug=0,  # noqa: ARG001\n     modulefinder_class=ModuleFinder,\n@@ -76,15 +80,17 @@ def _do_test(\n         ConstantsModule(), path=[test_dir.path, *path], **kwargs\n     )\n     if import_this.startswith(\"package:\"):\n-        finder.include_package(import_this.removeprefix(\"package:\"))\n+        module = finder.include_package(import_this.removeprefix(\"package:\"))\n     else:\n-        finder.include_module(import_this)\n+        module = finder.include_module(import_this)\n     if report:\n         finder.report_missing_modules()\n     modules = sorted(set(modules))\n-    found = sorted([module.name for module in finder.modules])\n+    found = sorted([m.name for m in finder.modules])\n     # check if we found what we expected, not more, not less\n     assert found == modules\n+    if module.error_msg:\n+        assert module.name in missing\n \n \n @pytest.mark.parametrize(\n@@ -112,6 +118,8 @@ def _do_test(\n         SCAN_CODE_IMPORT_CALL_TEST,\n         SCAN_CODE_IMPORT_MODULE_TEST,\n         SUB_PACKAGE_TEST,\n+        SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST,\n+        SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST_1,\n         SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST_2,\n         ZIP_EXCLUDE_TEST,\n         ZIP_INCLUDE_TEST,\n@@ -139,6 +147,8 @@ def _do_test(\n         \"scan_code_import_call_test\",\n         \"scan_code_import_module_test\",\n         \"sub_package_test\",\n+        \"SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST\",\n+        \"SYNTAX_ERROR_TEST_1\",\n         \"syntax_error_test_2\",\n         \"zip_exclude_test\",\n         \"zip_include_test\",\n", "problem_statement": "ImportError: Invalid syntax\n> I think I've found a similar error. \n> In the docstring of a function, I had an example of the response: I had the path to the main.py\n> \n> \n> ```\n> def get_exe_info() -> tuple[str, str, str]:\n>     \"\"\"\n>     This will return information on how the code was executed.\n>     # Exe: TODO\n>     # Script:\n>     # C:\\temp\\New folder (5)\\main.py\n>     # C:\\temp\\New folder (5)\n>     # main.py\n>     \"\"\"\n>     ...\n> ```\n> \n> \n> This causes the error:\n> \n> ```\n>   File \"C:\\temp\\New folder (5)\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 724, in include_file_as_module\n>     module = self._load_module_from_file(name, path, deferred_imports)\n>   File \"C:\\temp\\New folder (5)\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 542, in _load_module_from_file\n>     self._load_module_code(module, loader, deferred_imports)\n>     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n>   File \"C:\\temp\\New folder (5)\\.venv\\Lib\\site-packages\\cx_Freeze\\finder.py\", line 472, in _load_module_code\n>     raise ImportError(msg, name=name) from None\n> ImportError: Invalid syntax in main.py\n> ```\n> With python 3.14, cx freeze 8.5.3.\n> \n> \n> Is this the same error or should I raise a ticket?\n> Thanks \n\n _Originally posted by @TRWoodland in [#3206](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/issues/3206#issuecomment-3846582593)_\n", "hints_text": "As I said in [#3206 comment](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/issues/3206#issuecomment-3849156103):\n\n> Actually, in this case, it seems to me that the error is masked; it should be a SyntaxError, not an ImportError. I'll check if the message can be made clearer.\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "As I said in [#3206 comment](https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/issues/3206#issuecomment-3849156103):\n\n> Actually, in this case, it seems to me that the error is masked; it should be a SyntaxError, not an ImportError. I'll check if the message can be made clearer.\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/marcelotduarte/cx_Freeze/commit/de743b400633903e07f2a6542e8ffe7ab4b424a4"], "created_at": "2026-04-14T20:50:51Z"}
